Abstract: This document reports on a study conducted by System Development Corporation in early 1967, on the Thai National Police Department (TNPD).  The tactical missions of the TNPD -- control of  "normal" crime, subversion, and insurgency -- are dependent upon both operational and management effectiveness.  Optimum effectiveness in the acquisition, allocation and employment of resources is, in turn, dependent in large measure upon the development of a viable information system.  A program for the development of such a system is outlined in the report.  (Author abstract)

Abstract: This report explores the feasibility of establishing a new education center in the United States for participants from Latin America where the overall professional and personal environment would be more closely related to their special needs and requirements. The center's program would focus on improving the effectiveness of U.S. training for Latin American participants, particularly in the area of public administration.  A draft proposal was prepared and reacted to by various universities interested in participating in such a program.  While this report is not an evaluation, per se, it represents an approach to improve the relevance of U.S. training for students from Latin American countries.  (Author abstract)

Abstract: Project to produce and test modern mathematics textbooks and conduct teacher training activities in ten English-speaking African countries - Sierra Leone, Liberia, Ghana, Nigeria, Uganda, Kenya, Tanzania, Zambia, Ethiopia, and Malawi.  The Education Development Center (EDC) will implement the project. The project will conduct an 8-week workshop in Mombasa, Kenya, for 60 U.S. consultants and host country representatives to produce texts, teachers' guides, and tests for primary and secondary schools.  EDC will publish and distribute the texts for experimental testing in an average of 30 classes and/or teacher training institutes in each country.  A maximum of 140 elementary and secondary school teachers will be trained to use the materials in classroom instruction.  Students who have completed modern mathematics courses will be tested in order to assess the effectiveness of the materials.  When necessary, EDC will also provide consultation to host governments on planning wide-scale adoption or adaptation of the modern mathematics curricula developed by the project.

Abstract: USAID PROVIDES GENERAL SUPPORT TO HAILE SELASSIE I UNIVERSITY (HSIU) BY TOPPING SALARIES OF KEY US PERSONNEL AND TRAINING ETHIOPIAN PARTICIPANTS TO REPLACE THEM. ASSISTANCE IS CONCENTRATED IN AGRICULTURE, EDUCATION, PUBLIC HEALTH. GENERAL SUPPORT IS ALSO EXTENDED TO FACULTIES SUCH AS ARTS AND SCIENCES WHICH ARE NOT AREAS OF USAID CONCENTRATION BECAUSE THESE FACULTIES TEACH LARGE NUMBERS OF STUDENTS FROM COLLEGES OF EDUCATION AND BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION. GENERAL SUPPORT PROVIDED TO ADMINISTRATIVE DIVISIONS OF UNIVERSITY SUCH AS FINANCIAL AND BUSINESS AFFAIRS AND REGISTRAR'S OFFICE CONTRIBUTE TO OVERALL USAID OBJECTIVES. HIGHLY SELECTIVE PARTICIPANT TRAININING PROGRAM IS CONDUCTED TO ASSURE AVAILABILITY TO QUALIFD ETHIOPIAN STAFF TO MEET LIMITED NEEDS IN BASIC FACULTIES AND BROAD RANGE OF ADMINISTRATIVE REQUIREMENTS OF HSIS CENTRAL ADMINISTRATION. FUNDS ARE ALSO PROVIDED FOR CONSTRUCTION AND EQUIPPING JFK MEMORIAL LIBRARY IN ADDIS. 3/26/70 AND 10/29/70 PROPS CONSOLIDATE RESIDUAL OPEX AND PARTICIPANT TRAINING ELEMENTS OF 4 OTHER USAID HIGHER EDUCATION PROJECTS WITH THIS ONE. 10/29/70 PROP RECOMMENDS STEPS TO MATCH GRADUATES TO AVAILABLE JOBS. PROP SUPPORTS ETHIOPIAN GOVERNMENT'S PROGRAM TO INCREASE ENROLLMENT AND ESTABLISH SEVERAL BRANCH CAMPUSES. SOME INSTITUTION BUILDING ACTIVITIES SUCH AS CURRICULUM AND MATERIALS DEVELOPMENT ARE FUNDED UNDER 73 AMENDMENT. 74 PROAG CHANGES STRATEGY TO MAKE USAID FUNDS RELEASED BY PHASE OUT OF OPEX PERSONNEL AVAILABLE TO ETHIOPIAN STAFF FOR RESEARCH, SERVICE, AND MATERIALS/CURRICULUM DEVELOPMENT. RESPONSIBILITY FOR PROJECT MANAGEMENT SHIFTED WHEN HSIU BEGAN EXPERIMENT ON DIRECT MANAGEMENT OF 2 PARTICIPANTS. OTHER DONORS INCLUDE SWEDISH GOVERNMENT (CONSTRUCTION, EQUIPMENT, STAFFF OF BUILDING COLLEGE), WEST GERMAN GOVERNMENT (EQUIPMENT, STAFF OF COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING); WHO, UNICEF, MINISTRY OF OVERSEAS DEVELOPMENT, BRITISH COUNCIL, FORD FOUNDATION, AND OTHERS PROVIDE PERSONNEL. USAID CHIEF EDUCATION ADVISOR FUNDED UNDER THIS PROJECT SERVES AS PROJECT MANAGER, PROVIDES TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE, AND HELPS COORDINATE DONOR ACTIVITIES. ANOTHER ADVISOR MONITORS OPEX PARTICIPANT TRAINING.

Abstract: GRANT TO THE GOVT OF GUATEMALA TO STRENGTHEN ITS SOCIO-ECONOMIC PLANNING UNITS: THE NATL ECON PLANNING COUNCIL (CNPE), AND PLANNING SECTIONS OF THE MINISTRIES OF AGRICULTURE, EDUC, HEALTH, AND PUBLIC WORKS.PROJECT PROVIDES LONG & SHORT-TERM DIRECT HIRE AND CONTRACT AID STAFF CONSULTANTS (PLANNING & AGR ECONOMISTS AND SOCIAL SCIENTISTS)TO WORK WITH THESE AGENCIESIN THE PLANNING OR MODIFYING OF SECTOR DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS.PROJ ALSO PROVIDES SHORT-TERM TECH ASSISTANCE IN SUBJECT MATTER AREAS OF PARTICULAR WEAKNESS IN GOG PLANNING AGENCIES, NAMELY ECONOMETRICS AND MANPOWER PLANNING.PARTICIPANT TRAINING AT THE MA LEVEL IS FUNDED FOR 9 PROFESSIONAL PLANNERS CURRENTLY WORKING WITH THE MINISTRIES OR THE CNPE. SPECIFIC ACTIVITIES TARGETED FOR SUCH AID INVOLVEMENT ARE: 1.A 1971-75 NATIONAL DEVELOPMENT PLAN TO BE IMPLEMENTED UNDER THE GUIDANCE OF THE CNPE; 2.MODIFICATIONS TO THE AID LOAN-FINANCED RURAL PRIMARY EDUC PROGRAM AND RURAL DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM BY THE CNPE & THE MINISTERIAL PLANNING UNITS; 3.DEVELOPMENT OF FINANCIALLY-AFFORDABLE PLANS FOR A MAJOR EXPANSION OF PUBLIC EDUC & RURAL HEALTH EFFORTS FOR THEIR PRESENTATION TO INTERNATIONAL LENDERS INCLUDING AID.PROJECT-SUPPLIED US ADVISORS ASSIST GOG COUNTERPARTS WITH CONDUCTING PRELIMINARY FIELD RESEARCH AND STUDIES FOR THE DESIGN OF THESE PROGRAMS OR PLANS.4.NATURAL RESOURCE CONSERVATION & DEVELOPMENT ACTIVITIES(SUCH AS SEMINARS) TO BE PLANNED AND CONDUCTED WITH THE ASSISTANCE OF AID PROJECT-FUNDED LOCAL OR FOREIGN SCIENTIFIC CONSULTANTS.THESE CONSULTANTS MAY UNDERTAKE THE PREPARATION OF A NATIONAL SEMINAR ON PHYSICAL ECOLOGICAL DEVELOPMENT AND SCOPES-OF-WORK FOR FEASIBILITY STUDIES OF PROSPECTIVE RESOURCE DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS. THE PRIMARY BENEFICIARIES OF THIS PROJECT ARE GOG DEVELOPMENT PLANNERS AND THE AID MISSION PERSONNEL INVOLVED WITH GUATEMALAN SOCIO-ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS.

Abstract: GRANT TO THE CENTRAL AMERICA INSTITUTE FOR BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION (INCAE)  TO SUPPORT ITS DEVELOPMENT AS A VIABLE,INDIGENOUSLY+STAFFED & SUPPORTED REGIONAL INSTITUTION OFFERING GRADUATE LEVEL EDUCATION IN BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION.AID HAS SUPPORTED INCAE SINCE 1963 UNDER A PREVIOUS PROJECT THRU TECH ASSISTANCE CONTRACTS WITH HARVARD BUSINESS SCHOOL  (HBS)  PROFESSOR.DURING THIS 1963-67 PERIOD,HBS ADVISORS PROVIDED INSERV INSTRUCTION TO INDIG INCAE FACULTY,CONDUCTED SHORT COURSES & SEMINARS FOR SR BUSINESSMEN  (THE INCAE ADVANCED MGMT PROGRAM) ,HELPED PREPARE CASE STUDIES IN BUSINESS ADMIN,AND DEVISED PRELIMINARY PLANS FOR A PERMANENT GRADUATE INSTITUTE AT INCAE.THE REALIZATION OF THIS GRAD INSTITUTE IS THE FOCUS OF THIS SUBSEQUENT PROJECT. THROUGH PREVIOUS AID ASSISTANCE,INCAE HAS DEVELOPED A CORE ADMIN&FACULTY,AND THE FUND-RAISING NETWORK TO ENABLE EXECUTION OF THE PRESENT ACTIVITIES.THIS PROJ UNDERWIRTES THE CONTINUED SERVICES OF HBS ADVISORS TO ASSIST INCAE PERSONNEL WITH PREPARING ADDITIONAL CASE STUDIES AND MAINTAINING THE ADV MGMT PROG,PLUS DEVELOPING A LIBRARY AND PERFECTING THE GRAD LVL CURRICULUM.HBS ADVISORS CONTINUE THEIR TEACHER TRNG SERVICES & ADMIN ASSISTANCE.AID GRANT ALSO PROVIDES FACULTY SALARIES & RELATED EXPENSE COSTS,AND PARTICIPANT TRNG SCHLRSHPS FOR 3 FUTURE INCAE FACULTY MEMBERS.INCAE,THRU PRIVATE DONATIONS & A LOAN,CONSTRUCTS THE NECESSARY FACILITIES: CLASSRMS,FACULTY & STUDNT HOUSING,OFFICES,LIBRARY,AND DINING AREA. THIS PROJ WILL,IN EFFECT, BE ON A TRIAL BASIS FOR THE FIRST 2 YRS OF IMPLEMENTATION.BY THE END OF THIS PERIOD,INCAE SHOULD BE ABLE TO DEMONSTRATE IMMINENT VIABILITY,IE,IT MUST HAVE REGIONAL SUPPORT-EVIDENCED BY PRIVATE SECTOR DONATIONS & SUFFICIENT ENROLLMENT,AND MUST HAVE ITS 1ST GRAD LVL COURSE IN OPERATION.BY FY70,A SND GRAD LVL COURSE SHOULD BE UNDERWAY,LINKAGES WITH OTHER UNIVS ESTABLSHED,ENDOWMENT FUND TARGET ACHIEVED,AND NO OF INDIG FACULTY ON AN INCREASE.AID WOULD THEREUPON PROVIDE CONTINUED FINANCIAL &HBS ASSISTANCE THRU FY70 AND HBS ASSISTANCE THEREAFTER. PRIMARY BENEFICIARIES:CENTRAL AMERICA'S PROSPECTIVE BUSINESS ADMINISTRATORS. 12/70 PROP RECOMMENDS CONTINUED INCAE SUPPORT.

Abstract: Project to upgrade the College of Agriculture at Ethiopia's Haile Selassie I University.  Enrollment will be at least 500 and graduating classes in excess of 100.  Teachers will average 240 student credit hours and teach at least 12 credits/semester. Staff time devoted to research will be decreased and staff living conditions improved; 23 staff will receive participant training. Summer courses will be taught to rural service personnel.

Abstract: LOAN PROVIDED TO CENTRAIS ELECTRICAS BIASILEIRAS S.A. (ELETROBRAS) TO IMPROVE THE ABILITY OF BRAZILIAN ELECTRICAL UTILITIES TO OPERATE POWER SYSTEMS INTERCONNECTED BY EXTRA-HIGH VOLTAGE (EHV) TIES. LOAN WILL FINANCE DOLLAR COSTS OF US TRAINING FOR BRAZILIAN ELECTRICAL ENGINEERS AND MANAGEMENT OFFICIALS IN EHV AND INTERCONNECTED SYSTEM TECHNIQUES AS WELL AS TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO ELETROBRAS - A HOLDING CORPORATION FOR ALL POWER UTILITIES OWNED BY THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT. THE PARTICIPANT PROGRAM WILL TRAIN 10 GRADUATE ENGINEERS PER YEAR FOR A PERIOD OF 5 YEARS. THE 18-MONTH PROGRAM WILL CONSIST OF 6-MONTHS OF PREREQUISITE COURSES AT CATHOLIC UNIVERSITY OF RIO DE JANEIRO, FOLLOWED BY 2 SEMESTERS OF STUDY IN THE US AND 2 MONTHS OF PRACTICAL TRAINING WITH US POWER COMPANIES, POWER EQUIPMENT MANUFACTURERS, AND CONSULTING FIRMS IN THE POWER FIELD. TWO US CONSULTANTS WILL WORK WITH ELETROBRAS AND ITS SUBSIDIARIES FOR 2 YEARS. A POWER RATE SPECIALIST WILL CONCENTRATE ON THE DETERMINATION OF RATE LEVELS AND FORMS FOR THE MAJOR POWER CONSUMING INDUSTRIES. COUNTERPART PERSONNEL WILL RECEIVE ON-THE-JOB TRAINING IN POWER RATE DESIGN. THE OTHER CONSULTANT WILL BE A SPECIALIST IN POWER POOL OPERATION WHO WILL ASSIST ELETROBRAS IN PLANNING, ORGANIZING, AND RUNNING THE "OPERATING AND LOAD DISPATCH COMMITTEE" THAT IS BEING SET UP TO RUN THE INTEGRATED SOUTH CENTRAL POWER SYSTEM. THIS AND OTHER SUCH COMMITTEES ARE BEING FORMED TO EFFECT THE EFFICIENT OPERATION AND UTILIZATION OF THE RAPIDLY EMERGING EHV INTERCONNECTED POWER SYSTEMS. THEY WILL EVENTUALLY BE STAFFED BY PARTICIPANTS IN THE TRAINING PROGRAM BEING PARTIALLY FINANCED BY THIS LOAN.

Abstract: Project to assist the Regional Textbook Center of the Organization of Central American States (ODECA) in developing and producing free textbooks and teachers' guides in basic subjects for public elementary schools in Central America and Panama. The Textbook Center will complete a total of 33 manuscripts and proof editions for textbooks and teachers' guides in the subjects of reading, language, mathematics, social studies, and science, as well as negatives of the manuscripts for delivery to country Missions for in-country printing.  A U.S. consultant team will provide advice to the Textbook Center, participating Ministries of Education, and A.I.D. regional and country offices to assure adequate financing, contracting, and production of proof editions, negatives, and the end products.  The team will also provide TA to supervisory and administrative personnel within country Ministries of Education in the use of the textbooks and guides.

Abstract: AUDITS PROJECT ESTABLISHING THE ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT SPECIAL ACCOUNT (EDSA) TO ASSIST THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA (ROKG) IN CARRYING OUT ITS LONG-RANGE DEVELOPMENT PROGRAMS. AUDIT COVERS THE ENTIRE ROKG FY 1965 AND THE FIRST NINE MONTHS OF FY 66 AND INCLUDES A SELECTIVE REVIEW OF FINANCIAL REPORTS MAINTAINED AT ROKG MINISTRIES, PROVINCIAL HEADQUARTERS, REGIONAL BUREAUS, AND SPECIAL CITIES OFFICES. EDSA PROCEDURES REQUIRE THAT EDSA EXPENDITURE REPORTS BE SUBMITTED TO THE MISSION BY ROKG AGENCIES THROUGH THE MINISTRY OF FINANCE (MOF) IN ACCORDANCE WITH MOE INSTRUCTIONS. MANY ROKG AGENCIES, HOWEVER, HAD DIFFICULTY FOLLOWING INSTRUCTIONS; IN 18 INSTANCES, EXPENDITURES WERE REPORTED FOR WHICH THERE WERE NO SUPPORTING DOCUMENTS; LOWER REPORTING AGENCIES FAILED TO SUBMIT TIMELY, FACTUAL REPORTS TO HIGHER AGENCIES; AND SEVEN INSTANCES OF DUPLICATIVE REPORTING WERE DISCLOSED. IT IS RECOMMENDED THAT THE ACCOUNTING PROCEDURES SET FORTH IN A MANUAL PREPARED BY AN ACCOUNTANT BE IMPLEMENTED AS SOON AS POSSIBLE. TEN SITES AT 15 PROJECTS WERE INSPECTED TO VERIFY THAT EXPENDED EDSA FUNDS WERE USED ACCORDING TO THE INTENTION OF THE ACCOUNT. THE KOREAN RECONSTRUCTION BANK(KRB) MADE LOANS TO TWO FIRMS WHOSE FUNDS WERE USED TO REPAY PREVIOUSLY INCURRED DEBTS TO THE KRB. BECAUSE THESE FUNDS WERE USED INAPPROPRIATELY, THE AUDITORS ARE PRESENTING A BILL OF COLLECTION FOR THEM. IN MOST OTHER CASES, EDSA FUNDS WERE USED APPROPRIATELY. ALTHOUGH NO RECOMMENDATIONS ARE MADE FOR CORRECTIVE ACTION, THE EPB WILL SEEK TO PREVENT SIMILAR MISAPPROPRIATIONS. INSPECTION WAS MADE OF 22 PROJECTS INCLUDING THREE SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION PROJECTS. IN GENERAL, IMPLEMENTATION IS SATISFACTORY WITH THE EXCEPTION OF THREE PROJECTS UNDER THE DIRECTION OF THE MINISTRY OF EDUCATION (MOE). IT IS RECOMMENDED THAT INSTRUCTIONS BE GIVEN THE MOE TO ASSURE THAT CONSTRUCTION ON THESE PROJECTS IS PROPERLY PLANNED, SUPERVISED, AND IMPLEMENTED. THE ROKG SUBSIDY CONTROL LAW REQUIRES THAT ROKG AGENCIES INSTALL AND MAINTAIN SEPARATE ACCOUNTS FOR EDSA FUNDS RELEASED TO LOCAL AUTONOMOUS BODIES.  TWENTY-ONE LOCAL ROKG AGENCIES HAVE FAILED TO COMPLY AND A RECOMMENDATION IS MADE TO ENFORCE THE LAW.

Abstract: EVALUATES CONTRACTOR PERFORMANCE ON PROJECT IN PERU TO DEVELOP AN INTEGRATED OPERATING FRAMEWORK FOR PLANNING RESEARCH PROGRAMS BASED ON AN EFFICIENT DATA COLLECTION AND EVALUATION SYSTEM. NO METHODOLOGY IS INDICATED FOR EVALUATION, WHICH COVERS THE PERIOD 1/1/67-6/30/67. THE CONTRACT STAFF FROM IOWA STATE UNIVERSITY (ISU) EXCELLED IN RESEARCH FOR NON-OPERATIONAL AGENCIES, ITS HIGHEST PRIORITY. USAID, HOWEVER, PLACES PRIORITY ON THE SHORTER-TERM OBJECTIVES OF ADAPTING NEW POLICIES AND OPERATIONS INTO ACTIVE AGENCIES. EFFORTS DURING THIS REPORTING PERIOD HAVE BEEN DEVOTED TO ATTAINING A BETTER UNDERSTANDING, AMONG USAID, ISU, AND NORTH CAROLINA STATE UNIVERSITY (ALSO CONTRACTED UNDER THIS PROJECT), OF PROJECT OBJECTIVES AND ISU'S ROLE. TOWARD THIS END, A SIX-MONTH WORK PLAN WAS DEVELOPED FOR EACH TECHNICIAN; ISU PERSONNEL BEGAN WORKING ON HIGHER PRIORITY ASSIGNMENTS, INCLUDING PERFORMING IMMEDIATE SERVICES IN THE AREAS OF CREDIT AND MARKETING; AND LONG-RANGE GOALS ASSURING CLOSE WORKING RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN BOTH CONTRACT GROUPS HAVE BEEN ESTABLISHED. RESEARCH FOR THE NATIONAL PLANNING INSTITUTE WILL BE PHASED OUT GRADUALLY AND ISU WILL HELP THE MISSION PREPARE MACRO-ECONOMIC AND AGRICULTURAL SECTIONS OF THE PROGRAM MEMORANDUM. ALTHOUGH THE WORK OF INDIVIDUAL TECHNICIANS HAS BEEN OUTSTANDING, THE DEGREE OF ISU'S OVERALL COMMITMENT TO THE PROJECT IS QUESTIONABLE. EVALUATORS CONSIDER THAT THE ISU FIELD STAFF SHOULD RECEIVE MORE SUPPORT FROM THE HOME INSTITUTION, ESPECIALLY IN THE PROVISION OF DATA PROCESSING SYSTEMS, MARKETING LITERATURE AND MANUALS. THE ON-CAMPUS PROJECT DIRECTOR HAS INFORMED THE MISSION DIRECTOR THAT GREATER COMMITMENT TO THE PROJECT CAN BE EXPECTED. PROGRESS TOWARD PROJECT OBJECTIVES WILL BE MORE FULLY EXPLAINED IN THE NEXT EVALUATION. TO DATE, IMPROVEMENTS HAVE BEEN MADE IN PARTICIPANT TRAINING ACTIVITIES AND ADVANCES MADE AT THE NATIONAL FERTILIZER CORPORATION AND THE AGENCY FOR STATISTICS AND CARTOGRAPHY. PROGRESS IN OTHER AGENCIES HAS BEEN THWARTED DUE TO GOP BUDGETARY LIMITATIONS AND ORGANIZATIONAL WEAKNESS. THESE PROBLEMS MAY WORSEN IN LIGHT OF THE PERUVIAN FISCAL SITUATION.

Abstract: RESULTS WITH GLANDLESS COTTONSEED FLOUR WERE SOMEWHAT PARADOXICAL. COMPARED TO MODIFIED COW'S MILK, THE ABSORPTION AND RETENTION OF NITROGEN WERE DISTINCTLY SUPERIOR TO WHAT WOULD HAVE BEEN EXPECTED WITH "DEGOSSYPOLIZED" COTTONSEED FLOUR. RATES OF WEIGHT GAIN ALSO WERE SUPERIOR AND THE LEVELS OF SERUM ALBUMIN ATTAINED WERE QUITE COMPARABLE TO THOSE FROM "DEGOSSYPOLIZED" COTTONSEED FLOUR IN OTHER SUBJECTS. IN THESE STUDIES, AS WELL AS IN THE INITIAL TREATMENT OF MALNOURISHED INFANTS, THERE WAS A MORE PRONOUNCED TENDENCY FOR SODIUM TO BE RETAINED AND A DISTINCTLY GREATER TENDENCY TO DEVELOP PELLAGRA-LIKE MANIFESTATIONS. ALTHOUGH THE LATTER IS SUSPECTED OF BEING RELATED TO THE UNAVAILABILITY OF TRYPTOPHAN, INADEQUATE FOR PYRIDINE NUCLEOTIDE SYNTHESIS, THIS CANNOT BE PROVED AT THIS TIME. BASED ON THESE STUDIES, HOWEVER, IT IS BELIEVED THAT AS PART OF A MIXTURE CONTAINING NATURAL FOODS, THIS COTTONSEED FLOUR WOULD PROVE SUPERIOR TO THOSE FROM ORDINARY COTTONSEED MEAL WHICH HAS BEEN "DEGOSSYPOLIZED" BY PHYSICAL OR CHEMICAL METHODS.

Abstract: THE USE OF THICK-SMEAR SLIDES FOR THE INDIRECT FLUORESCENT ANTIBODY (IFA) TEST FOR MALARIA APPEARS TO HAVE DISTINCT ADVANTAGES OVER THIN BLOOD FILMS WHICH HAVE BEEN EMPLOYED FOR THIS PURPOSE. THE TECHNIQUE FOR PREPARATION OF THE THICK ANTIGEN SLIDES IS AS FOLLOWS: 1) DRAW BLOOD FROM DONOR WITH A HEPARINIZED SYRINGE; 2) REMOVE THE PLASMA BY CENTRIFUGATION AND WASH THE CELLS FIVE TIMES IN BUFFERED PHYSIOLOGICAL SALINE (PH 7.2); 3) RESUSPEND CELLS IN BUFFERED PHYSIOLOGICAL SALINE, SO THAT THICK SMEARS PREPARED FROM THE SUSPENSION GIVE AT LEAST 10 OR MORE PLASMODIA TO EACH HIGHPOWER FIELD; 4) PREPARE THICK SMEARS ON MICROSCOPE SLIDES AND AIR DRY AT ROOM TEMPERATURE; 5) STORE AT -70 C UNTIL NEEDED. THE IFA TEST IS PERFORMED AS FOLLOWS: 1) REMOVE SLIDES FROM STORAGE, PLACE IN STAINING RACKS, AND IMMERSE IN GLASS DISTILLED WATER FOR 10 MINUTES ON A SLOWLY MOVING SLIDE ROTATOR; 2) DRAIN AND AIR DRY AT ROOM TEMPERATURE; 3) IMMERSE IN ACETONE AT -20 C FOR 30 MINUTES, DRAIN, AND AIR DRY (THIS STEP MAY BE OMITTED); 4) PLACE SLIDES IN MOIST CHAMBER, OVERLAY AMOUNTS WITH SERUM DILUTIONS TO BE TESTED, AND INCUBATE 30 MINUTES AT 37 C; 5) PLACE IN RACKS IN BUFFERED PHYSIOLOGICAL SALINE, AND WASH ON A SLIDE ROTATOR FOR 15 MINUTES; 6) DRAIN, AIR DRY, AND REPLACE IN MOIST CHAMBER; 7) OVERLAY WITH THE APPROPRIATE DILUTION OF ANTI-SPECIES CONJUGATE MIXED WITH EVANS BLUE, 1:500; 8) INCUBATE 30 MINUTES AT 37 C; 9) WASH AS IN STEP 5; 10) DRAIN, AIR DRY, AND MOUNT WITH BUFFERED GLYCERIN AND A COVER SLIP; 11) READ ON A FLUORESCENCE MICROSCOPE EQUIPPED WITH BG-12 (TO LOCATE PLASMODIA) AND UG-2 (TO EVALUATE SPECIFIC FLUORESCENCE) EXCITER FILTERS AND AN OG-1 (OR EQUIVALENT) BARRIER FILTER. THE SEVERAL ADVANTAGES OF THIS TECHNIQUE ARE DISCUSSED.

Abstract: AIRGRAM FROM USAID/BRAZIL NOTES THAT THE CONTRACTOR'S THIRD QUARTER REPORT FOR 1967 IS INFORMATIVE AND ADEQUATELY DESCRIBES THE CONTRACTOR'S WORK ON BEHALF OF THE UNIVERSITY GRANDE DO SUL. 3 AREAS WHERE CONSIDERABLE PROGRESS IS BEING MADE ARE RESEARCH, COMMUNICATIONS AND TEACHING. ADVANCED SOIL TESTING METHODS DEVELOPED IN COOPERATION WITH UNIVERSITY PERSONNEL ARE BEING ADAPTED BY OTHER SOIL TESTING LABORATORIES, AND A PROGRAM OF AGRICULTURAL COMMUNICATION IS BEING ADVANCED. THE CONTRACTOR'S STAFF IS ENGAGED IN TEACHING GRADUATE COURSES AND GIVING GUIDANCE TO BOTH STUDENTS AND FACULTY MEMBERS. IT WAS NOTED THAT THE CONTRACTOR'S CONCERN ABOUT THE LAG IN THE RELEASE OF CONTAP FUNDS FOR LOCAL PROGRAM NEEDS WAS BROUGHT TO THE ATTENTION OF THE MISSION; CAUSE OF DELAY WAS CLARIFIED. IT WAS ALSO NOTED THAT THE CONTRACTOR'S REPORT DID NOT ADEQUATELY DISCUSS PARTICIPANT TRAINING IN RELATION TO PROJECT OBJECTIVES. PARTICIPANT TRAINING IS, HOWEVER, BEING IMPLEMENTED IN HARMONY WITH PROJECT PLANS.

Abstract: LOAN IS EXTENDED TO GOVT OF PERU TO ASSIST IN MODERNIZATION OF FOOD MARKETING SYSTEM. $5 MILLION IS USED TO ESTABLISH A TRUST FUND IN THE INDUSTRIAL BANK FOR THE PURPOSE OF MAKING SUB-LOANS (BOTH SHORT AND LONG TERM) TO EXPANDING SUPERMARKET CHAINS AND FOR THE WHOLESALERS OR OTHER ORGANIZERS OF VOLUNTARY CHAINS OR ASSOCIATIONS OF GROWING "BODEGAS" (SMALL FOOD STORES) AND "SUPERETTES". $500,000 IS USED FOR EQUIPMENT AND TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE FOR CONAP, THE GOVT FOOD MARKETING AGENCY (FOR GRADES AND STANDARDS, MARKET INFORMATION AND A FOOD INDUSTRY VOCATIONAL SCHOOL) AND TO FINANCE A NON-PROFIT MARKET RESEARCH CROP. AS WELL AS FOR THE STUDY OF THE ADEQUACY OF THE PRESENT WHOLESALE MKT AND A PILOT COOP MKT PROJECT.

Abstract: LOAN TO ASSIST SENEPA OF GOP IN 1967-74 MALARIA ERADICATION PROGRAM (MEP). MEP A SEQUEL TO EARLIER PROGRAMS AND UTILIZES PREVIOUS EPIDEMIOLOGICAL & ENTOMOLOGICAL RESEARCH AS TACTICAL BASE. ADMINISTRATED & ORGANIZED BY SENEPA WITH ADVISORY ASSISTANCE BY PASA/USPHS, MEP IMPLEMENTS FOUR PHASES: 1.PREPARATORY-ORGANIZATIONAL & PERSONNEL DEVELOPMENT 2.ATTACK-HOUSES SPRAYED,LARVICIDING,CASE TREATMENT 3.CONSOLIDATION-SURVEILLANCE ACTIVITIES TO SEEK OUT & TREAT RESIDUAL INFECTION AND MONITOR DISEASE OUTBREAKS 4.CONTINUATION-SENEPA INTEGRATED INTO GOP HEALTH SERVICE AND ANTI-MALARIA RESPONSIBILITIES TURNED OVER TO LOCAL HEALTH SERVICES. ADDITIONALLY FUNDED & ASSISTED BY GOP PAHO/WHO & UNICEF.

Abstract: PROJECT CONSTRUCTS GENERATING PLANT CONSISTING OF TWO 16.5 MEGAWATT (MW) GENERATING UNITS AND STEP-UP SUBSTATION AT BASE OF EXISTING KAJAKAI DAM. 129 MI OF TRANSMISSION LINES CARRY POWER TO 3 SUBSTATIONS WHICH STEP DOWN VOLTAGE. PROJECT IS INCORPORATED INTO LOCAL SYSTEM WHICH CONSISTS OF SMALL HYDRO AND DIESEL GENERATING STATIONS WITH TOTAL CAPACITY OF 6 MW. AID PROJECT ADDS 33 MW TO SYSTEM AND TRAINS MANAGERIAL AND OPERATIONAL PERSONNEL  COST OVERRUNS NECESSITATED SEVERAL AMENDMENTS TO ORIGINAL LOAN. PRICE OF PROJECT INFLUENCED BY DISTURBANCES, UNSETTLED CONDITIONS IN SOUTH ASIA IN 1971-1972.

Abstract: RESEARCH STUDY CONDUCTED BY A SUB-PROJECT CONTRACTOR, THE STATE UNIV OF NEW YORK(SUNY), ON THE PROBLEMS CONFRONTING BRAZIL'S PRIMARY EDUCATION PROGRAM AND THE MEANS FOR INCREASING ENROLLMENT AND REDUCING DROP-OUT & REPETITION. SUB-PROJ WAS INTENDED TO RESEARCH VARIOUS PROBLEM AREAS IN THE EDUC PROGRAM AND ASSIST INDIVIDUAL STATES WITH THE PLANNING & IMPLMNTATN OF CORRECTIVE PROGRAMS. INFO FOR THIS REPORT WAS DEVELOPED THRU STUDIES OF MIN OF EDUC DATA. IT WAS DISCOVERED THAT 85% OF BRAZILIAN CHILDREN WHO ENTER THE 1ST GRADE DROP OUT BEFORE COMPLETING THE 4TH GRADE WITH THE HIGHEST COMBINED DROPOUT RATE BEING FOR 1ST GRADE STUDENTS. THE FAILURE RATE OF FIRST GRADE STUDENTS IS ALSO THE HIGHEST(34%). THE ACUTENESS OF THE 1ST GRADE FAILURE/DROPOUT PROBLEM IS DUE TO SEVERAL FACTORS: 1)OVER HALF OF THE PRIMARY ENROLLMENT IS IN THE 1ST GRADE; 2)THE RANGE OF AGES OF 1ST GR STUDENTS IS VERY BROAD(7-14); 3)FACTORS(1) & (2) MAKE THE 1ST GR THE MOST DIFFICULT GRADE TO TEACH YET THE LEAST QUALIFIED TCHRS ARE ASSIGNED TO THIS GRADE. A FACTOR ADVERSELY AFFECTING ALL PRIMARY GRADES IS THAT ALTHOUGH 82% OF EDUC SYS ENROLLEES ARE IN THE PRIMARY GRADES,ONLY 43% OF GOB FUNDING IS ALLOCATED TO PRIMARY SCHLS. POSSIBLE STRATEGIES FOR REDUCING DROPOUT & REPET ARE: 1)ENFORCING SCHL ATTENDANCE LAWS; 2)CHANGING CRITERIA FOR GRADE PROMOTION FROM THOSE BASED SOLELY ON ACCOMPLSHMNT TO THOSE WHICH CONSIDER THE AGE OF THE STUDENT; 3)UTILIZING INCENTIVES FOR ENRLLMNT,EG,A SCHL LUNCH PROG; 4)IMPROVING THE INSTRUCTIONAL PROG. ALTHOUGH SCHLS COULD PHYSICALLY HANDLE THE SUDDEN INCREASE IN ENRLLMNT RESULTING FROM ENFORCED ATTNDNCE LAWS BY UTILIZING A MULTI-SHIFT SCHEDULE,THE TEACHING PROG COULD NOT ACCOMMODATE THIS ABRUBT CHANGE. THE SUNY TEAM THEREFORE RECOMMENDED THE FOLLOWING 5-YR PROGRESSIVE PLAN: 1ST YR -- ESTABLSH AUTOMATIC GRADE PROMOTION,REVISE 1ST GR CURRIC,ORIENT TCHRS TO NEW PROG; 2ND YR -- ENFORCE ATTNDNCE OF 7-YR OLDS,REVISE 2ND GR CURRIC,ORIENT 2ND GR TCHRS TO NEW PROG; 3RD YR -- ENFORCE ATTNDNCE OF 8-YR OLDS,REVISE 3RD GR CURRIC,ORIENT 3RD GR TCHRS; 4TH YR -- ENFORCE ATTNDNCE OF 9-YR PLDS,REVISE 4TH GR CURR,ORIENT TCHRS; 5TH YR -- ENFORCE 10-YR OLDS ATTNDN

Abstract: REVIEWS THE MAIN CONSIDERATIONS IN EVALUATING THE EFFECTS OF RESEARCH PROGRAMS ON CROP PRODUCTION IN DEVELOPING NATIONS. INTERNATIONALLY SPONSORED AGRICULTURAL RESEARCH FOR DEVELOPING NATIONS HAS GROWN TO INCLUDE SIX ACTIVE INTERNATIONAL INSTITUTES; THREE MORE ARE UNDER DEVELOPMENT, AS ARE TWO RELATED PROGRAMS. THIS REPORT FOCUSES ON HIGH YIELDING VARIETIES OF WHEAT AND RICE AND OUTLINES THE DIRECT AND INDIRECT EFFECTS ON OUTPUT, CITES THE PROBLEMS OF LINKING RESEARCH WITH CHANGES IN PRODUCTION, AND EXAMINES SEVERAL MAJOR APPROACHES TO MEASUREMENT. CHANGES IN AREA AND YIELD IN COUNTRIES ADOPTING THE HIGH-YIELDING VARIETIES ARE EXPLORED. TWO COMPLEX TOOLS FOR ASSESSING THE EFFECT ON PRODUCTION -- PRODUCTION FUNCTION AND INDEX NUMBER ANALYSIS -- ARE OUTLINED; BOTH THESE TYPES OF ANALYSIS CAN BE IMPROVED BY REFINING TECHNIQUES AND IMPROVING DATA. THE REPORT CONCLUDES BY REVIEWING THE NEED FOR MORE RESEARCH AND ADDITIONAL FUNDING.

Abstract: Discusses the concept of institution building as an approach to the understanding of induced social change.  It also seeks to identify operational methods and action strategies helpful to practitioners and to persons actively engaged as change agents in cross-cultural situations.  "institution" is defined as a change-inducing and change-protecting formal organization.  The institution building approach has a social engineering bias.  Its root proposition is that a large proportion of the significant contemporary changes, especially in the developing countries, are deliberately planned and guided and can be distinguished from those that occur through gradual evolutionary processes or as the consequences of political or social revolution.  It was decided that the most effective and feasible test of the research approach would be through case studies of field experiences which would permit the gathering and analysis of empirical data according to the concepts developed by the institute building program.  The four cases selected were the college of education of the university of nigeria, the Central University of Ecuador, the Institute of Public Administration at Thammasat University in Thailand, and the Institute of Public Administration for Turkey and the Middle East.  The results of these studies represent an important increment to the knowledge of the processes of induced social change and a significant testing of the institution building research approach.  This paper analyzes and compares the more salient findings, suggests implications for the program's general approach to the institution building process, and indicates future development of theory, methodology, and practical application.

Abstract: THE PUBLIC ADMINISTRATION INSTITUTE FOR TURKEY AND THE MIDDLE EAST (PAITME) BEGAN IN 1953 WITH THE INTENTION OF TRAINING AND EDUCATING CIVIL SERVANTS. LITTLE WAS CERTAIN ABOUT ITS MISSION OR ITS IMMEDIATE FUTURE. IT WAS TO TEACH, PERFORM RESEARCH, AND FURNISH DOCUMENTATION IN PUBLIC ADMINISTRATION, BUT IT HAD NO DOCTRINE OR PROGRAM. THIS DOCUMENT DESCRIBES THE ORIGIN OF THE INSTITUTE, THE WORKING GROUP, AND THE PROGRESS DURING THE FIRST ELEVEN YEARS. BY 1954, THE ORGANIZATION WAS IN THREE SECTIONS: TRAINING, RESEARCH AND DOCUMENTATION. TRAINING AND EDUCATIONAL ACTIVITIES HAD ASSUMED A HEAVILY ACADEMIC CAST WITH EMPHASIS ON LARGE CLASSES, LECTURES, EXAMINATION, AND LESSER AMOUNT OF CONTACT WITH THE REAL WORLD OF ADMINISTRATION. THE EVENTS OF THE DECADE FROM 1954-1964 ARE ORGANIZED IN TERMS OF PAITME'S LEADERSHIP, RESOURCES, PROGRAM, AND EXTERNAL RELATIONSHIPS. THE REPORT INDICATES THAT THE CHALLENGE OFFERED BY THE UNITED NATIONS IN THE EARLY FIFTIES FOR TURKEY TO CREATE ITS OWN EXPLICIT DOCTRINE OF PUBLIC ADMINISTRATION HAS NOT BEEN FULFILLED. CONCLUDES THAT THE INSTITUTE HAS NOT BEEN A STRONG FORCE IN THE SEARCH FOR SUCH A DOCTRINE OR IN DISEMINATING NORMS IN THE FIELD OF PUBLIC ADMINISTRATION.

Abstract: LOAN IS PROVIDED TO THE TURKIYE SINAI KALKINMA BANKASI (TSKB), A PRIVATE INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT BANK,TO PROMOTE THE EXPANSION & DEVELOPMENT OF TURKEY'S PRIVATE INDUSTRIAL SECTOR. TSKB WILL PROVIDE MEDIUM & LONG-TERM FORIEGN EXCHANGE AND TURKISH LIRA FUNDS FOR PRIVATE INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS. THESE SUBLOANS WILL FINANCE THE PROCUREMENT OF US MATERIALS (WHICH ARE UNAVAILABLE IN TURKEY) AS WELL AS US CONSULTANT SERVICES FOR TSKB'S SUB-BORROWERS. IN ITS LENDING PROGRAM,THE BANK WILL GIVE PREFERENCE TO INVESTMENTS WHICH WILL FAVORABLY INFLUENCE THE BALANCE OF PAYMENTS, WHICH WILL SUPPORT ESSENTIAL CONSUMER GOODS INDUSTRIES AND TO THOSE WHICH WILL ENCOURAGE ENTERPRENEURS TO MAXIMIZE INVESTMENT IN THE PRIVATE INDUSTRIAL SECTOR. ITS EQUITY PARTICIPATION POLICY WILL ALSO REVOLVE UPON A STATED SET OF OBJECTIVES: 1)TO INCREASE THE CAPITAL OF UNDER-CAPITLAIZED PRIVATE FIRMS; 2)TO ENCOURAGE THE DEVELOPMENT OF A CAPITAL MARKET BY SELLING ITS SHARES WEN POSSIBLE; 3)NOT TO HOLD MORE THAN 25% OF A FIRM'S CAPITAL; AND 4)TO RENDER TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE BUT NOT TO INTERFERE WITH A COMPANY'S MANAGEMENT WHILE SERVING ON ITS BOARD OF DIRECTORS. TOURISM OR MINING PROJECTS WILL NOT BE FINANCED. HOST COUNTRY WILL PROVIDE PERSONNEL AND INSTITUTIONAL INFRASTRUCTURE. PRIMARY BENEFICIARIES ARE OWNERS OF PRIVATE INDUSTRIAL ENTERPRISES FOR WHOM INCREASED LOANS AND CAPITALIZATION FOR THEIR COMPANIES WILL BE AVAILABLE.

Abstract: Loan is provided to the Government of Brazil to expand the Santa Cruz thermal plant of Central Eletrica de Furnas to accommodate anticipated industrial growth. Equipment, materials and services financed under the loan will have their sources and origin in the United States, except Brazilian engineering services in the event of a joint venture. The expansion will involve a net addition of 480 megawatts to the existing l60 megawatt plant, which was originally constructed with A.I.D. financing (project 5120258). This addition will include two 200-megawatt oil-fired turbine generators, a switchyard and a 132-kilovolt substation extension, plus three additional l32-kilovolt transmission circuits on double circuit steel towers to interconnect with the FURNAS system at Jacarepagua. Some 194 additional employees will be added to the power plant staff to accommodate the expansion.  Training of these staff members has been under way for about a year as part of the AID-financed first stage project, both locally and at the 464-megawatt Piratininga thermal plant outside of Sao Paulo. Further training under this loan will take place at these locations as well as in the U.S. and Puerto Rico (on a limited basis). The additional energy produced by the Santa Cruz plant as a result of this expansion will complement the hydroelectric plants in the area, including six AID-recipient utility companies which will be able to purchase bulk power from the Santa Cruz plant to compensate for low functioning in dry seasons and to use in uncompleted construction projects.  Because of this resultant interdependency of the area's power plants, provisions for telecommunications systems between them are to be added later under this loan. The Santa Cruz expansion should bring energy production in south central Brazil up to capacity for filling energy needs estimated for l972.

Abstract: LOAN IS PROVIDED TO GOVT OF TURKEY TO FINANCE A DETAILED APPRAISAL OF MINERAL RESOURCES AND TO IMPROVE THE CAPACITY OF THE MINERAL RESEARCH AND EXPLORATION INSTITUTE (MTA) TO MAP, EXPLORE AND EVALUATE TURKISH MINERAL RESOURCES. MTA GEOLOGISTS WILL BE TRAINED BY US GEOLOGICAL SURVEY PERSONNEL WHILE COOPERATING IN THE IMPLEMENTATION OF TWO OR MORE EXPLORATION SUBPROJECTS. SELECTION OF AREAS OF EXPLORATION, ONE OR MORE FOR IRON ORE AND ONE OR MORE FOR NON-FERROUS MATERIALS, WILL BE BASED ON THEIR RELATIVE INDICATED POTENTIAL FOR THE MINERAL SOUGHT. BOTH FERROUS AND NON-FERROUS EXPLORATION ACTIVITIES WILL BE STARTED AT THE SAME TIME AND WILL BE CONDUCTED CONCURRENTLY. FOLLOWING THIS ACTIVITY, A BROAD-SCALE GEOLOGIC INVESTIGATION, SUPPORTED IF NECESSARY BY GEOPHYSICAL TESTING, WILL BE IMPLEMENTED IN THE DESIGNATED AREAS. AS A RESULT OF THIS INVESTIGATION, THE MOST PROMISING AREAS WILL BE SELECTED FOR DETAILED MAPPING AND INTENSIVE EXPLORATION AS WARRANTED. SELECTION WILL BE BASED ON OBSERVED MINERALIZATION, GEOCHEMICAL AND GEOPHYSICAL ANOMALIES,AND GEOLOGICAL ENVIRONMENT. FOR IRON ORE, INTENSIVE AIRBORNE SURVEYS WILL BE UNDERTAKEN BY MTA WHERE REQUIRED TO RECHECK ANOMALIES DETERMINED BY PREVIOUS SURVEYS, OR TO TEST LOCALITIES NOT COVERED PREVIOUSLY. AERIAL PHOTOGRAPHS WILL ALSO BE USED TO COMPILE PHOTOGRAMMETRIC BASE MAPS OF THE MORE FAVORABLE LOCALITIES. TRAINING PROVIDED TO MTA GEOLOGISTS WILL INCLUDE PHOTOGEOLOGY, GEOLOGIC MAPPING, INTERPRETATION OF GEOLOGIC CONDITIONS, CORE DRILLING, CORE LOGGING AND SAMPLING, INSTALLATION OF LABORATORY EQUIPMENT, MINERAL DEPOSIT APPRAISAL, AND MAP AND REPORT PREPARATION. PROJECT ALSO INCLUDES PROCUREMENT OF CHEMICAL AND EXTRACTIVE METALLURGICAL EQUIPMENT, GEOPHYSICAL EQUIPMENT, DRILLING EQUIPMENT, AND PRINTING EQUIPMENT. EQUIPMENT SELECTED FOR PROCUREMENT WILL BE REVIEWED AND APPROVED IN ADVANCE BY THE USGS TO ASSURE ITS ADEQUACY FOR THE PLANNED TRAINING AND EXPLORATION EFFORT.

Abstract: LOAN TO THE INSTITUTO DE FOMENTO NACIONAL (NATIONAL DEVELOPMENT INSTITUTE-INFONAC), AN AUTONOMOUS DEVELOPMENT AND CREDIT AGENCY OF THE GOVERNMENT OF NICARAGUA WILL BE MADE AVAILABLE FOR RE-LENDING AND EQUITY INVESTMENT TO SUPPORT EXPANSION OF MEDIUM AND LARGE SCALE INDUSTRY. INFONAC LOANS WILL BE EXTENDED TO APPROXIMATELY 100 NEW AND EXISTING INDUSTRIES. LOANS WILL BE FOR PERIODS RANGING FROM TEN TO FIFTEEN YEARS AT INTEREST RATES NOT TO EXCEED 10%. EQUITY INVESTMENTS WILL BE MADE IN INDUSTRIES WHOSE POTENTIAL RETURN TO THE NATIONAL ECONOMY IS GREAT BUT WHICH CANNOT ARRANGE COMMERCIAL CREDIT. IN THESE CASES, INFONAC WILL TAKE AN ACTIVE ROLE IN DIRECTING AND DEVELOPING COMPANIES UNTIL EQUITY CAN BE SOLD TO PRIVATE INVESTORS. ALL SUBLOANS AND EQUITY INVESTMENTS DERIVED FROM AID FUNDS WILL PROVIDE FOREIGN EXCHANGE FOR PURCHASE OF US GOODS AND SERVICES. UP TO 5% OF AID LOAN WILL FINANCE COSTS OF US CONSULTANTS AND TECHNICIANS WHO WILL WORK WITH INFONAC IN IMPROVING ITS OWN ORGANIZATION AND ADMINISTRATION AND IN UPGRADING STAFF CAPABILITIES IN PROJECT SELECTION, ANALYSIS, PROMOTION, AND IMPLEMENTATION. INFONAC CREDIT ACTIVITIES WILL BE CONCENTRATED ON FIRMS WHICH USE THE HIGHEST COMPONENT OF NICARAGUAN RAW MATERIALS AND ON VERTICAL INTEGRATION INDUSTRIES (I.E., INDUSTRIES WHICH PRODUCE GOODS OTHER NICARAGUAN INDUSTRIES CAN USE). IN ADDITION TO DOUBLING THE AMOUNT OF INDUSTRIAL CREDIT AVAILABLE, INFONAC PROGRAM WILL INCREASE THE NUMBER OF MEDIUM AND LARGE INDUSTRIES FROM 97 TO 200; INCREASE GROSS ANNUAL INDUSTRIAL PRODUCTION BY 40%; INCREASE FOREIGN EXCHANGE EARNINGS/SAVINGS BY 13%; AND INCREASE THE SIZE OF THE ACTIVE INDUSTRIAL FORCE BY 30%.
Ancilary Data: Loan no. 524-L-009

Abstract: CONTRACT FUNDS ARE PROVIDED TO THE UNIVERSITY OF WISCONSIN (UOW) FOR A RESEARCH PROJECT TO DETERMINE THE BENEFITS RESULTING FROM INCREASED ECONOMIC COOPERATION AMONG COUNTRIES OF SOUTHEAST ASIA AND THE CONDITIONS REQUIRED TO REALIZE THESE BENEFITS. A RESEARCH TEAM WILL BE ORGANIZED AROUND A STAFF OF UOW ECONOMISTS AND WILL INCLUDE US AND SOUTHEAST ASIAN EXPERTS IN THE ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT OF SOUTHEAST ASIA WHO HAVE FILLED SHORT-TERM RESEARCH APPOINTMENTS AT UOW, CONSULTANT LECTURERS SPECIALIZING IN RELATED DISCIPLINES AND REGIONS, AND REGULAR UOW STAFF. AID'S OFFICE OF PROGRAM COORDINATION WILL MONITOR THE CONTRACT. RESEARCH WILL BE CONDUCTED ON THE COUNTRIES OF THE ECAFE REGION AND ON JAPAN, AUSTRALIA AND CHINA AS THEY IMPINGE ON THE REGION. SYSTEMATIC RESEARCH WILL BE CARRIED OUT IN THE FOLLOWING MAJOR AREAS: (1) THE THEORY AND EXPERIENCE, WITH PARTICULAR APPLICATION TO SOUTHEAST ASIA, OF ECONOMIC GROWTH; (2) THE THEORY AND EXPERIENCE OF ECONOMIC COOPERATION FOR ECONOMIC GROWTH; (3) THE NATURE AND EXTENT OF EXISTING ECONOMIC INTERDEPENDENCE IN SOUTHEAST ASIA; (4) THE PROBABLE IMPACT OF CLOSER COOPERATION FOR INDIVIDUAL COUNTRIES ON THE PRODUCTION OF INDIVIDUAL COMMODITIES, EXPORTS AND IMPORTS, GOVERNMENTAL REVENUES, AND NATIONAL ECONOMIC PLANS; (5) THE ROLE OF NATIONAL AND REGIONAL INSTITUTIONS AND PROGRAMS IN PROMOTING ECONOMIC GROWTH IN SOUTHEAST ASIA; (6) THE NON-ECONOMIC FACTORS AFFECTING NATIONAL AND REGIONAL GROWTH IN SOUTHEAST ASIA; (7) ALTERNATIVE STRATEGIES OF ASIAN GOVERNMENTS, THE US AND OTHER DEVELOPED COUNTRIES, AND PRIVATE ORGANIZATIONS, WHICH WOULD ACCELERATE ECONOMIC GROWTH IN THE REGION. SPECIAL ACTIVITIES TO BE UNDERTAKEN IN CONNECTION WITH THE PROJECT INCLUDE ATTENDANCE (AND POSSIBLY PRESENTATION OF PAPERS) AT THE CONFERENCE ON ECONOMIC PLANNING IN SOUTHEAST ASIA AT THE EAST-WEST CENTER, UNIVERSITY OF HAWAII, BY TEAM MEMBERS; AND A WORKING CONFERENCE IN ASIA.

Abstract: FIVE PHASE LOAN TO GOVERNMENT OF ETHIOPIA SUPPORTS 14 YEAR PROGRAM TO ERADICATE MALARIA, TO BE CARRIED OUT BY MALARIA ERADICATION SERVICE (MES) WITH THE ASSISTANCE OF AID AND WHO. COUNTRY DIVIDED INTO 4 ZONES (A-D) EACH OF WHICH WILL UNDERGO 4 STAGE ERADICATION ACTIVITIES (WORK IN AREA B FOLLOWS COMMENCEMENT OF WORK IN "A" BY 2 YEARS; C FOLLOWS D BY 2 YEARS, ETC.). DURING PREPARATORY STAGE I GEOGRAPHIC RECONNAISSANCE CONDUCTED TO IDENTIFY ALL HOMES AND RELATED STRUCTURES, PREPARE MAPS AND ITINERARIES, DELINEATE MALARIOUS AREAS AND COLLECT ENTOMOLOGICAL AND EPIDEMIOLOGICAL DATA. ALL HOUSES SPRAYED TO PREVENT MOSQUITOES FROM TRANSMITTING MALARIA PARASITES FROM INFECTED TO NON-INFECTED PEOPLE. DURING ATTACK PHASE, HUMAN DWELLINGS AND PROXIMATE ANIMAL SHELTERS SPRAYED 1-3 TIMES YEARLY; EVALUATIONS CONDUCTED AND EXTENSIVE ACTIVE CASE DETECTION UNDERTAKEN, PASSIVE CASE DETECTION ACTIVITIES ESTABLISHED IN CLINICS AND HOSPITALS. CONSOLIDATION PHASE EMPHASIZES MALARIA SURVEILLANCE TO RESERVOIR OF INFECTIVE CASES AND CONFIRM COMPLETE ERADICATION MAINTENANCE STAGE STRESSES CONSOLIDATION OF MES AND BASIC HEALTH SERVICES. INTERVENTION BASED ON ELIMINATION OF PARASITE RESERVOIR IN HUMANS RATHER THAN CONTROL OF MOSQUITO IN BREEDING LOCATIONS. CAP FOR THIRD TRANCHE OF LOAN CHANGES SCOPE OF PROJECT FROM MALARIA ERADICATION TO MALARIA CONTROL CITING IEG/WHO/AID STRATEGY REVIEW TEAM APPRAISAL MAY 1970. SCOPE OF SPRAYING ACTIVITIES REDUCED; FEWER NEW AREAS SERVED; EMPHASIS UPON PRESENTLY MALARIOUS ZONES RATHER THAN BORDERLINE AREAS. IMPROVED FIELD METHODOLOGIES (SPRAYING, GEOGRAPHICAL RECONNAISSANCE AND SURVEILLANCE) ARE MAJOR GOALS. DURATION OF ASSISTANCE IS INDEFINITE. MERGING OF MES AND BHS STRESSED. ALSO PROVIDES EXTENSIVE BACKGROUND. CAP OF 5/12/75 PRESENTS REVISED PROJECT.

Abstract: LOAN TO GOP TO PROVIDE IMPROVEMENTS TO 2.8 KM OF THE TOCUMEN HIGHWAY. PROJECT ONE OF FOUR CONSTRUCTION PROJECTS UNDERTAKEN BY THE SECOND INCREMENT TO THE "PANAMA-SPECIAL PROGRAM" EFFORT EVOLVING IN 1966 AND STRESSING LABOR-INTENSIVE METHODS TO PROVIDE EMPLOYMENT & UPGRADE TRANSPORTATION & SANITATION SYSTEMS. IMPROVEMENTS TO TOCUMEN HIGHWAY INCLUDE: 1.ADDING TWO LANES PLUS A GRASS MEDIAN STRIP 2.IMPROVING DRAINAGE 3.CONSTRUCTING CURBING, SIDEWALKS, GUTTERS, BUS STOP TURN-OUTS,SIDEWALKS, LEFT TURN STORAGE LANES & INTERCHANGES 4.BUILDING A BRIDGE AT THE EAST END OF PROJECT TO CARRY WIDENED HIGHWAY. PROJECT IMPLEMENTED BY CAMINOS, AEROPUERTOS Y MUELLES UNDER THE GOP MINISTRY OF PUBLIC WORKS.

Abstract: LOAN TO GOVERNMENT OF GUATEMALA WILL HELP SUPPORT IMPROVEMENT OF THE GOG'S SYSTEM OF PROPERTY TAX APPRAISAL,  MAPPING, ASSESSMENT, AND COLLECTION. PROJECT WILL AFFECT A 12,000 SQ KM AREA OF THE PACIFIC COAST PLAIN, AND 27 MAJOR URBAN CENTERS THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRY. PROPERTY IDENTIFICATION MAPS (MOSAICS) WITH OVERLAYS SHOWING PROPERTY BOUNDARIES, OWNERSHIP, LAND USE, AND GENERAL LAND CAPABILITY WILL BE PRODUCED BY THE NATIONAL GEOGRAPHIC INSTITUTE (IGN), WHICH WILL ALSO PLACE A NETWORK OF SURVEY CONTROL MONUMENTS THROUGHOUT THE AREA FOR SUBSEQUENT LEGAL CADASTER. GERMAN TECHNICAL MISSION TO CENTRAL AMERICA WILL TRAIN IGN STAFF IN PRODUCTION OF 1/1000 SCALE URBAN MOSAICS, AND WILL SUPERVISE THEIR PRODUCTION. ADDITIONAL IGN RESPONSIBILITIES DURING PROJECT INCLUDE ASSIGNMENT OF PROPERTY IDENTIFICATION NUMBERS; INVESTIGATION OF PROPERTY BOUNDARIES, REGISTRATION, AND OWNERSHIP; AND MAINTENANCE OF PROPERTY RECORDS. USAID-SUPPORTED CONSULTANTS WILL ASSIST THE TAXATION OFFICE OF THE MINISTRY OF FINANCE (RENTAS) IN SEVERAL AREAS. CONSULTANTS WILL DEVELOP ORGANIZATIONAL/FUNCTIONAL CHART FOR RENTAS AND ACCOMPANYING PROCEDURAL MANUAL WHICH WILL DETAIL EMPLOYEE FUNCTIONS. TAX APPRAISAL MANUAL, DRAWING UPON THOSE USED ELSEWHERE IN CENTRAL AMERICA, WILL BE DEVELOPED, AS WILL LAND VALUE MAPS, PROPERTY RECORD CARDS, ASSESSMENT NOTICES, AND BILLING FORMS. RENTAS AND CONSULTANT FIELD PERSONNEL WILL COLLECT FIELD DATA AND APPLY MANUAL AND VALUE MAP STANDARDS TO DETERMINE ASSESSMENT. ASSESSMENT ROLLS WILL BE COMPILED, AND LATER TRANSCRIBED TO AN AUTOMATED SYSTEM FOR SUBSEQUENT BILLINGS. PROJECT WILL SHIFT TAX BURDEN FROM LOWER AND MIDDLE ECOMOMIC ECHELONS TO THE LARGE PROPERTY HOLDERS OF IDLE LAND.

Abstract: LOAN TO THE GOVT OF TURKEY PROVIDES BASIC MEDICAL EQUIPMENT AND SUPPLIES(STERILIZERS, SURGICAL & DIAG TABLES, UTENSILS, LIGHTS, OSCILLOSCOPES, SPECIMENS, ETC) TO THE ATATURK UNIV MEDICAL SCHOOL (AUMS) AND ITS AFFILIATE, THE ERZURUM PROVINCIAL HOSPITAL (EPH). PROJECT IS BEING UNDERTAKEN IN CONJUNCTION WITH A GOT-SUPPORTED FACILITIES EXPANSION/RENOVATION PROGRAM AT AUMS & EPH. MOST OF THE EQUIPMENT TARGETED FOR AUMS WILL BE PLACED IN THE 3 NEW MED SCIENCE BLDGS UNDER CONSTRUCTION AND WILL BE USED IN ITS 5-YR MED EDUC (PHYSICIAN TRAINING) PROGRAM. LOAN-FUNDED EQUIPMENT TO EPH WILL BE USED TO OUTFIT X-RAY, RADIO THERAPY, EMERGENCY & SURGICAL OPERATION ROOMS, CLINICAL LABS, AND PHYSICAL MEDICINE & REHABILITATION WARDS. AUMS WILL DRAW TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS FOR THIS EQPMNT, WILL INVITE BITS FROM EQPMNT SUPPLIERS, AND ANALYZE OFFERS. IT WILL BE ASSISTED BY A FOREIGN PURCHASING SPECIALIST FROM HACETTEPE MEDICAL SCHOOL. ASSISTANCE WITH ACTUAL EQPMENT PROCUREMENT WILL BE PROVIDED LOAN-FUNDED US CONSULTANTS. AUMS HAD ORIGINALLY REQUESTED PARTICIPANT TRAINING UNDER A RELATED AID TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE PROJECT (2770428). THIS TRAINING WOULD BE FOR APPROX 21 TURKISH PARTICIPANTS AT A US UNIV; AREAS OF STUDY WOULD INCLUDE HOSPITAL ADMINISTRATION, BIOCHEMISTRY, ANATOMY, PHARMACOLOGY, DIETETICS, SURGICAL SCIENCE, MEDICAL INSTRUMENT ELECTRONICS, AND MICROBIOLOGY. FUNDING FOR THIS TRAINING WILL BE PROVIDED BY THIS PROJECT, HOWEVER, UNLESS EQUIVALENT TRAINING BECOMES AVAILABLE UNDER 2770428 OR ANOTHER PROJECT. AS AUMS DRAWS MOST OF ITS ENROLLMENT FROM THE EASTERN PROVINCES OF TURKEY, AS GRADUATES FROM AUMS ARE EXPECTED TO REMAIN IN THIS REGION, AND AS EPH PROVIDES MEDICAL SERVICES TO THE PEOPLE OF THIS REGION, THIS PROJECT'S PRIMARY BENEFICIARIES ARE THE PEOPLE OF TURKEY'S EASTERN PROVINCES.

Abstract: This report is a second synthesis of the observations and recommendations of the Education and Human Resource Development Committee's Nigerian Project Task Force, which have been in the process of formulation since early 1965.  A summary report, this paper does not include substantiation of all faints: it is meant to present an overview of the Task Force's observations, to support recommendations for AID's (Agency for International Development) program of assistance to Nigeria. The paper is also submitted in this preliminary form to promote a more intensive discussion of Nigerian human resource development and utilization within AID, between AID and the Nigerian Project Task Force, and between these groups and those Nigerians in policy-making positions. The first section of the report, "General Perspectives," discusses the concept of human resource development and utilization, the Nigerian economy and its divers sectors, and the spectacular progress and persistent problems.  Section II discusses education-oriented institutions, training-oriented elements, and strategy for modern sector education and training.  Sections III and IV deal with employment generation and education and training for the less-developed sectors. Concluding remarks in Section V point out the need to mobilize the nation's total resources for achievement of a more balanced pattern of development.  (ERIC abstract)

Abstract: This report, prepared by a labor economist and manpower specialist after about seven weeks of observation and consultation, aims to evaluate the extensive USAID (United States Agency for International Development) Mission education and training activities in relation to a realistic view of the current and future manpower needs in Afghanistan, and to determine what steps should be taken for this purpose.  The introduction and list of specific proposals are followed by a general discussion of: (1) the Afghan setting; (2) the primacy of agriculture; (3) comments on the education system; (4) literacy and language; (5) middle level skills; (6) the Kabul University; (7) initiative and enterprise; (8) womanpower; (9) manpower planning; (10) a Human Resource Development program; (11) the labor market, occupations, and the wage structure.  (ERIC abstract)

Abstract: EVALUATES THE PERFORMANCE OF THE BRAZILIAN ELEMENTARY EDUCATION PROJECT AS IMPLEMENTED IN THE STATE OF MINAS GERIAS FOR THE PERIOD 4/20/64-12/31/66. PROJECT WAS INTENDED TO UPGRADE SCHOOL FACILITIES AND THE TEACHING & SUPERVISORY PROGRAMS. INFORMATION FOR THIS EVAL WAS DEVELOPED THRU REVIEWS OF RECORDS, DISCUSSIONS WITH USAID/B & STATE GOVT OFFICIALS, AND ON-SITE INSPECTIONS. ALTHOUGH 355 CLASSROOMS WERE TARGETED FOR CONSTRUCTION, RECONSTRCTN,OR REPAIR,WORK WAS ACCOMPLISHED ON ONLY 13. NONE OF THE 6 SUPERVISORY CENTERS PLANNED WERE CONSTRCTD,NOR ANY OF THE 8 MEDICAL/DENTAL UNITS ESTABLISHED. CONTRIBUTING TO THESE SHORTFALLS WERE INFLATION AND WORK DELAYS CAUSED BY SUDENE'S LAXITY IN APPROVING PLANS. THE MAJOR FACTOR,HOWEVER,WAS LACK OF SUFFICIENT FUNDING. SUDENE  (THE LOAN RECIPIENT & ADMINISTRATOR) WAS ABLE TO RELEASE ONLY NCR $366,596 OF THE PLEDGED NCR $642,994 TO THE STATE IMPLEMENTING AGENCY,THE COMISSAO DE EDUCACAO NA AREA MINEIRA DO PLOIGONO DAS SECAS  (CEPOL). THE REMAINDER OF THE FUNDS, IF RELEASED,WOULD BE USED TO COMPLETE PAYMENTS TO CARRPE,THE STATE-OWNED AGENCY RESPONSIBLE FOR SCHOOL CONSTRCTN & RENOVATION,AND TO FINISH THE HALF-CONSTRCTD NORMAL SCHOOL AT PORTEIRINHA. IT IS RECOMMENDED THAT USAID/B RELEASE THE REMAINING FUNDS TO SUDENE  (WHICH, IN TURN, COULD RELEASE THESE FUNDS TO CEPOL) BUT ONLY AFTER CEPOL OBTAINS THE NECESSARY ADDITIONAL FINANCING FROM THE GOB MIN OF EDUC, THE STATE OF MINAS GERAIS, AND SUDENE TO COMPLETE THE NORMAL SCHOOL. THE CONSTURCITON WORK THAT WAS ACCOMPLISHED WAS OF GOOD QUALITY. ALTHOUGH A MAINTENANCE PROGRAM DID NOT EXIST AT THE OF EVALUATION, SUCH A PROGRAM WAS ASSURED AFTER TERMININATION OF CONTRUCTION. TRAINING ACCOMPLISHMENTS FELL FAR SHORT OF GOALS WITH THE ADULT/ADOLESCENT LITERACY TRNG COMPONENT BEING ELIMINATED ALTOGETHER. INSUFF FUNDING WAS A FACTOR HERE ALSO; FUNDS THAT WERE USED TO COVER COST OVERRUNS FOR VEHICLE PURCHASES WERE TAKEN FROM TRNG FUNDS. EQPMNT/VEHICLE PROCUREMENT FOLLOWED ACCEPTIBLE PRACTICES,ALTHOUGH EQPMNT WAS PURCHASED FOR 2 SCHLS UPON WHICH CONSTRUCN WAS CANCELLED. THIS EQPMNT,PRESENTLY WAREHOUSED,SHOULD BE DISTRUBTED TO OTHER  AREAS IN THE POLYGON OF DROUGHT.

Abstract: SUMMARIZES ACCOMPLISHMENTS AND PROBLEMS OF PROJECT TO DEVELOP IMPROVED PLANNING AND ADMINISTRATIVE CAPACITY WITHIN THE MINISTRY OF EDUCATION AND STATE SECRETARIATS OF EDUCATION IN BRAZIL DURING THE PERIOD 10/01/-10/31/67. SELF-EVALUATION COMPILED BY THE PROJECT TEAM DISCUSSES ACTIVITIES IN 4 STATES, BAHIA, ESPIRITO SANTO, MINAS GERAIS AND RIO GRANDE DO SUL. PROGRESS IN ALL STATES IS DEEMED SATISFACTORY. MAJOR ACTIVITIES DURING THE PERIOD INCLUDE 1)VISITS TO ALL 4 STATES, 2)A MEETING OF REPRESENTATIVES FROM THE 4 STATES AT EPEM HEADQUARTERS, 3)SEVERAL MEETINGS OF EPEM, AT TIMES INCLUDING USAID OFFICIALS AND, 4)DEVELOPMENT OF ADDITIONAL GUIDELINES. SEVERAL PROBLEMS, HOWEVER, WERE ENCOUNTERED. IN ALL STATES EXCEPT RIO GRANDE DO SUL,THE COORDINATION IS WEAK AND EPEM MUST WORK INTENSIVELY TO INSURE EFFECTIVE COORDINATION. IN ADDITION,ALTHOUGH DATA COLLECTION IS PROGRESSING SMOOTHLY, CERTAIN KINDS OF INFORMATION ARE DIFFICULT TO FIND IN ALL OR MOST STATES (FINANCIAL DATA, DATA ON EQUIPMENT AND TEACHING MATERIALS, CONDITION OF SCHOOL BUILDINGS AND DETAILS ON ADMINISTRATIVE PERSONNEL). MAJOR PROBLEM FACING EPEM IN THE NEAR FUTURE WILL BE THE ORGANIZATION OF SEPARATE REPORTS FROM THE 4 STATES INTO A COHESIVE SECTOR LOAN PAPER.

Abstract: This report attempts to determine:  1) whether participants are applying their training toward improvement of agriculture; 2) to what extent they have returned to their former jobs or changed to other fields; and 3) whether they remain sympathetic to U.S. objectives after exposure to U.S. training and other experiences. One hundred and five returned participants who had studied in the United States between January 1958 and December 1966 were surveyed along with other relevant individuals.  This limited study (only 22 participants were actually interviewed) contains no specific recommendations but strongly stresses the need for the Moroccan Government to solve the degree equivalency problem.  This was a major issue, morale and otherwise, for returning participants with U.S. degrees which were not being adequately recognized. (Author abstract)

Abstract: This report is one of twenty-three country studies conducted as part of the worldwide survey of returned participants in accordance with AID/W instructions and guidelines contained in ICATO Circular A-175, November 1959.  The major purpose of this global effort was to obtain an overview of how the participant training program was progressing to ascertain ways in which future training might be more effective at the country, AID/W, and training institution levels.  This country study involved interviews using structured questionnaires with 164 returned participants, and discussions with 56 supervisors. Recommendations are implied in the findings in the areas of training design and support services.  (Author abstract)

Abstract: This report is one of twenty-three country studies conducted as part of the worldwide survey of returned participants in accordance with AID/W instructions an guidelines contained in ICATO Circular A-175, November 1959.  The major purpose of this global effort was to obtain an overview of how the participant training program was progressing to ascertain ways in which future training might be more effective at the country, AID/W, and training institution levels.  The study involved oral interviews with 364 participants who had returned to Kenya by January 1966.  Supervisors of returnees were also interviewed. While there was very little in the way of useful recommendations in this study, there were suggestions in the areas of training design and support services.  (Author abstract)

Abstract: EVALUATES THE PERFORMANCE OF A SUB-PROJECT OF THE BRAZILIAN ELEMENTARY & BASIC EDUC PROJECT AS IMPLEMENTED IN THE STATE OF BAHIA FOR THE PERIOD 7/27/63-12/8/66. THIS SUB-PROJ WAS DESIGNED TO UPGRADE THE QUALITY OF INSTRUCTION IN PRIMARY SCHLS AND RENOVATE/CONSTRUCT ADDITIONAL SCHL FACILITIES. INFORMATION FOR THIS EVAL WAS DEVELOPED THROUGH EXAMINATIONS OF FINANCIAL RECORDS AND DISCUSSIONS WITH USAID & BRAZILIAN STATE OFFICALS. AT TIME OF EVAL,WORK HAD BEEN INITIATED ON ONLY 11.5% OF THE CLASSROOMS TARGETED FOR CONSTRUCTION; ONLY 2% HHAD BEEN COMPLETED. AS 55% OF THE FUNDS BUDGETED FOR CONSTRCTN HAVE BEEN DISBURSED,PROJ IS EXPECTED TO FALL SHORT OF GOALS. ONLY 1 OF 20 INDUSTRIAL ARTS WRKSHPS WILL BE ABLE TO BE BUILT; NONE OF THE PLANNED REGIONAL SUPERVISORY CNTRS,TCHR,TRNG CNTRS,OR CURRIC & SUPERVISION CNTR WILL BE CONSTRUCTED. HIGH INFLATION WAS THE MAYOR FACTOR IN THESE SHORTFALLS. SECONDLY,THE STATE COMMISSION IN CHARGE OF ADMINISTERING PROJ LACKED SUFFICIENTLY-QUALIFIED PERSONNEL TO HANDLE A PROGRAM OF THIS MAGNITUDE. THIRDLY,STATE CONSTRCTN CONTRACTORS WERE INCAPABLE OF ADEQUATELY EXECUTING THE CONSTRUCTION. AFTER UNSUCCESSFULLY ATTEMPTING TO OBTAIN SUFFICIENT CONTRACT WORK,THE STATE COMMISSION TURNED CONSTRCTN RESPONSIBILITIES OVER TO THE MAYORS OF TOWNS IN WHICH SCHLS WERE TO BE BUILT. THE QUALITY TO WORKMANSHIP OF MAYOR-BUILT SCHLS WAS MUCH BETTER THAN THAT OF CONTRACTOR-BUILT SCHLS. COMPLETED CLASSROOMS WEREBEING USED & MAINTAINED ALTHOUGH NO FORMAL MAINT PROGRAM EX ISTED. PENDING PROJ DISBURSEMENTS WILL BE USED TO PROVIDE A WATER SUPPLY TO THE 26 COMPLETED SCHLS WHICH PRESENTLY LACK THIS CONVENIENCE. RECONSTRCTN WORK WAS DISCONTINUED AFTER 12O OF THE TARGETED 1002 CLASSRMS HAD BEEN RENOVATED DUE TO LOW COST-EFFECTIVENESS. THE SMALL AMT OF FUNDING BUDGETED BY THE STATE FOR TRNG RESULTED IN SHORTFALLS IN THE NUMBER OF LAY TEACHERS,TECH PERSONNEL,AND SUPERVISORS TRAINED DURING EVAL PERIOD,RESPECTIVELY: 3000 PLANNED, 248 ACTUAL; 130 PL,19 AC;100 PL,57 AC. 3496 ADULTS DID RECEIVE LITERACY TRNG NOT ANTICIPATED UNDER IMPLEMENTATION PLAN. THE HIGH-LEVEL PERSONNEL WHO RECEIVED US TRNG APPEARED TO BE UNDERUTILIZED.

Abstract: LOAN IS PROVIDED TO THE CENTRAL AMERICAN BANK FOR ECONOMIC INTEGRATION (CABEI) TO PROVIDE FINANCING TO INDIVIDUAL CENTRAL AMERICAN COUNTRIES FOR INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT SUB-PROJECTS WHICH ARE OF POTENTIAL ECONOMIC BENEFIT TO THE ENTIRE REGION. CABEI WILL FINANCE 100% OF THE ENGINEERING AND CONSTRUCTION COSTS OF THE SELECTED SUB-PROJECTS. INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT INCLUDING HIGHWAYS,ELECTRICAL POWER INTERCONNECTIONS,GRAIN STORAGE,INDUSTRIAL PARKS,PORTS AND INLAND WATERWAYS,TELECOMMUNICATIONS,AIRPORTS,IRRIGATI ON AND EDUCATIONAL FACILITIES WILL BE ELIGIBLE FOR FINANCING. HIGHWAY CONTRUCTION AND IMPROVEMENT WILL BE EMPHASIZED. 24 HIGHWAY SUB-PROJECTS TOTALING 1563 KILOMETERS ARE CURRENTLY PLANNED. CABEI WILL FINANCE A TOTAL OF 8 PORT AND INLAND WATER-WAY SUB-PROJECTS IN EL SALVADOR, HONDURAS, NICARAGUA AND COSTA RICA. SUB-PROJECTS RELATING TO CONSTRUCTION/INSTALLATION OF ELECTRICAL INTERCONNECTIONS ARE ALSO PLANNED FOR THE ABOVE-LISTED COUNTRIES. CONSTRUCTION OF INDUSTRIAL PARKS AND GRAIN SILOS WILL BE FINANCED IN GUATEMALA, HONDURAS, NICARAGUA AND COSTA RICA. AIRPORT RUNWAY IMPROVEMENT PROJECTS WILL BE IMPLEMENTED IN HONDURAS AND COSTA RICA AND 2 IRRIGATION SUB-PROJECTS ARE PLANNED IN HONDURAS AND NICARAGUA. A TELECOMMUNICATIONS NETWORK WILL BE ESTABLISHED IN CENTRAL AMERICA WITH CABEI DESIGNATING FUNDS FOR CONSTRUCTION/INSTALLATION OF THE BACKBONE OF THE OF THE SYSTEM AS WELL AS INTERCONNECTIONS AND DISTRIBUTION LINES TO THE MORE DENSELY POPULATED AREAS THROUGHOUT LATIN AMERICA. HIGHER-LEVEL EDUCATION INSTITUTIONS WILL RECEIVE SUPPORT IN EXPANDING THEIR FACILITIES, BOTH US AND CENTRAL AMERICAN FIRMS WILL BE CONTRACTED FOR ENGINEERING AND CONSTRUCTION SERVICES. CENTRAL AMERICAN COUNTRIES WILL ALSO CONTRIBUTE TO CABEI'S INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT FUND.

Abstract: LOAN, TECH ASSIST & EQUIPMENT ARE PROVIDED TO THE KOREA ELECTRICAL CO (KECO) TO CONSTRUCT A NEW THERMAL POWER GENERATING UNIT TO EXPAND KOREA'S SOURCES OF ELECTRICAL POWER SUPPLY. A NEW 200MW, OIL-FIRED, SINGLED UNIT THERMAL GENERATION STATION WILL BE CONSTRUCTED AT ULSON CITY (YONGNOM THERMAL POWER PLANT). COMMON FACILITIES WILL BE PROVIDED FOR THE LATTER ADDITION OF 2 OR MORE LIKE-SIZED UNITS. APPROXIMATELY 4KM OF 154KV TRANSMISSION LINE WILL BE INSTALLED CONNECTING THE PLANT TO THE HIGH VOLTAGE NETWORK AT KECO'S ULSON SUBSTATION. THE NEW THERMAL STATION WILL SUPPLY POWER FOR INDUSTRIAL PLANTS, FOR LIGHTING & FOR AGRICULTURAL USES. USAID WILL ALSO FINANCE US ENGINEERING SERVICES. IN ADDITION TO THE STATION'S ENGINEERING DESIGN,THE US ENGINEERING FIRM WILL PROCURE US EQUIPMENT & PROVIDE ON-SITE ENGINEERING TRNG & SUPERVISION DURING THE STATION'S INITIAL OPERATION & PERFORMANCE TESTING. 1 OR MORE US ENGINEERS WILL ASSIST KECO PERSONNEL TO PREPARE THE STATION'S OPERATION & MAINTENANCE PROCEDURES. ALSO THE FIRM WILL PREPARE & DELIVER A PERFORMANCE & TESTING PROCEDURES COORDINATION BOOKLET TO GUIDE KECO PERSONNEL DURING THE TESTING OF THE STATION'S MAJOR MECHANICAL & ELECTRICAL EQUIP AND IN OVERALL STATION PERFORMANCE TESTS. KECO WILL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR CONSTRUCTION OF THE STATION. IT WILL,HOWEVER,CONTRACT SEPARATELY WITH ANOTHER US FIRM FOR CONSTRUCTION ADVISORY SERVICES. THE US FIRM WILL ASSIST IN OVERALL CONSTRUCTION MGMT & PROCEDURES,LOCAL CONSTRUCTION CONTRACTING,PROCUREMENT OF NON-MAJOR US EQUIP & SUPPLIES AND RELATIONS AT THE SITE WITH US SUPPLIERS. THE FIRM WILL ALSO PLAN THE USE OF CONSTRUCTION EQUIP,WAREHOUSING,HEAVY EQUIP SETTING,RIGGING,STEEL ERECTION,MATERIALS HANDLING AND PROVIDE FINANCIAL MGMT & CONTROL. USAID-FINANCED EQUIP WILL INCLUDE A STEAM GENERATING UNIT(BOILER) & FANS,BOILER FEED PUMPS,COMBUSTION CONTROL EQUIP,WATER TREATING EQUIP,TURBO-GENERATOR,CONDENSOR,LAB EQUIP,OUTDOOR SUBSTATION & SPARE PARTS. WEST GERMANY WILL FINANCE 2ND 200MW THERMAL UNIT FOR THE PLANT. PRIMARY BENEFICIARIES ARE OWNERS OF INDUSTRIAL ENTERPRISES & LOCAL CITIZENS & FARMERS FOR WHOM INCREASED ELEC POWER WILL BE PROVIDED.

Abstract: USAID LOAN TO GOVERNMENT OF REPUBLIC OF TURKEY ASSISTS FINANCING FOREIGN EXCHANGE COSTS OF EQUIPMENT, SUPPLIES, SERVICES, & SCHOLARSHIPS FOR HACETTEPE SCIENCE CENTER (HSC). US CONTRACTOR (OVERSEAS EDUCATION SERVICE OF EDUCATION AND WORLD AFFAIRS) ASSISTS HSC IN DETERMINING EQUIPMENT AND STAFFING NEEDS, ARRANGES PARTICIPANT TRAINING & VISITING PROFESSORS, AND SERVES AS FUNDING CONDUIT TO MINIMIZE US INVOLVEMENT. LOAN SUPPORTS 100 MAN-YEARS ADVISOR SERVICES, 125 OF PARTICIPANT TRAINING, ACQUISITION OF LIBRARY MATERIALS & TEXTS, AND EXTENSIVE EQUIPMENTS FOR FACULTIES OF MED, HLTH SCI, & NATURAL/SOCIAL SCI.

Abstract: PURPOSE OF PROPOSED PROJECT IS TO CORRECT EXISTING DEFICIENCIES IN HIGHWAY DEPARTMENTS OF SOUTHERN STATES. TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE WILL BE PROVIDED TO REORGANIZE STATE HIGHWAY DEPARTMENTS AND IMPROVE MANAGEMENT, PLANNING, PROGRAMMING AND ADMINISTRATION. ENGINEERING CRITERIA, STANDARDS AND PROCEDURES TO BE ESTABLISHED FOR BOTH MAINTENANCE AND CONSTRUCTION. TRAINING PROGRAMS DEVELOPED FOR THE USE AND CARE OF EQUIPMENT, SHOP FACILITIES, MATERIAL WAREHOUSES, PARTS, DEPOTS.

Abstract: LOAN TO AUTONOMOUS MOGADISCIO WATERWORKS AGENCY (AMWA) FOR DESIGN, CONSTRUCTION OF MUNICIPAL WATER SUPPLY SYSTEM WITH CAPACITY OF 7.4 MILLION GAL/DAY; PROVIDES FOR CITY WATER NEEDS TO 1980. PROJECT PROVIDES MANAGEMENT SERVICES DURING INITIAL OPERATIONS OF AMWA AND PARTICIPANT TRAINING IN MAINTENANCE, MANAGEMENT, OPERATIONS. AMWA LATER BECAME NATIONAL WATER AGENCY AND ASSUMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR OPERATION OF ELECTRIC UTILITY.

Abstract: LOAN TO GOVERNMENT OF HONDURAS FINANCES MAJOR OVERHAUL OF EXISTING SECONDARY EDUCATION SYSTEM. PRIMARY FOCUS OF LOAN ISCONSTRUCTION AND EQUIPPING OF 453 NEW SECONDARY CLASSROOMS IN 15 OF NATIONS 17 DEPARTMENTS. SPECIFICALLY,CONSTRUCTION WILL RESULT IN REBUILDING AND EXPANSION OF 5 EXISTING OFFICIALPUBLIC SCHOOLS, CONSTRUCTION OF 4 NEW OFFICIAL SCHOOLS IN AREAS OF MAJOR POPULATION CONCENTRATION AND CONVERSION OF 11 SEMI-OFFICIAL SCHOOLS TO OFFICIAL STATUS. LOAN ALSO FUNDS CONSTRUCTION OF NEW PHYSICAL FACILITY FOR THE ESCULA SUPERIOR DE PROFESORADO (ESP), THE NATIONAL TEACHER TRAINING INSTITUTE, TO ALLOW A TRIPLING OF ENROLLMENT, PROVISION OF TEXTS, FURNISHINGS, LIBRARY BOOKS, AND LABORATORY EQUIPMENT CONSTITUTES 2ND LOAN COMPONENT. UNDER TA COMPONENT, LOAN WILL FINANCE US UNIVERSITY TEAM ASSISTANCE IN REORGANIZING AND IMPROVING THE ADMINISTRATION AND CURRICULUM OF ESP. SPECIALISTS IN AREAS OF ADMINISTRATION, CURRICULUM DEVELOPMENT, MATH/SCIE NCE, GUIDANCE, EDUCATIONAL RESEARCH AND TEACHER EDUCATION WILL CONDUCT INSERVICE TRAINING FOR APPROXIMATELY 370 ESP AND MOE STAFF AND TEACHERS. US TRAINING WILL BE PROVIDED TO AN ADDITIONAL 30 FROM ABOVE GROUPS. 4 PILOT SCHOOLS WILL BE ESTABLISHED TO TEST APPLICABILITY OF A COMPREHENSIVE HIGH SCHOOLPATTERNED AFTER US SCHOOLS WITH EMPHASIS PLACED UPON FREE CHOICE AND CURRICULUM MOBILITY RATHER THAN EARLY SPECIALIZATION. LOAN AMMENDMENT 12/6/71 DELETES TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE COMPONENT OF PROJECT. TELEGRAM-1 9/27/73 CHANGES SCOPE OF PROJECT TO CALL FOR CONSTRUCTION OF NOT LESS THAN 16 NEW OFFICIAL SECONDARY SCHOOLS. LOAN AMENDMENT OF 1/17/74 ELIMINATES REVAMPING OF EXISTING SEMI-OFFICAL SCHOOLS AND REPLACES TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE CLAUSE AND GUARANTEES THAT GOH WILL FINANCE (ORCAUSE TO BE FINANCED) A NEW FACILITY FOR ESP. TELEGRAM-2 9/ 27/73 CITES COST  OVERRUNS ON SCHOOL CONSTRUCTION AND DELETES CONSTRUCTION OF ESP FACILITY FROM US OBLIGATION.

Abstract: PROJECT CONSISTS OF COMPREHENSIVE PROGRAM TO UPGRADE LIVESTOCK INDUSTRY. CREATES DAIRY CROSSBREEDING RANCH IN TSETSE-FREE ZONE. ARTIFICIALLY INSEMINATED INDIGENOUS COWS PRODUCE CROSSBRED OFFSPRING WHICH ARE SOLD TO PRIVATE RANCHES. EXOTIC BREEDS OF DAIRY CATTLE PRODUCED ON EXISTING BREEDING FARMS ARE TRANSFERRED TO YOUNG-STOCK REARING FARMS CREATED BY PROJECT. DAIRY FARMERS BUY STOCK AT PRODUCTIVE AGE. ARTIFICIAL INSEMINATION SERVICES ARE EXPANDED, PERMITTING USE OF FEW HIGH QUALITY SIRES FOR BREEDING MANY COWS AT REDUCED COSTS. MODERN DAIRY FARM EQUIPMENT IS SUPPLIED ON EASY TERMS. TICK CONTROL CENTERS ARE ESTABLISHED. TSETSE CONTROL CREATES NEW GRAZING LAND; 5 MOBILE VACCINATION UNITS CONTROL EPIDEMIC DISEASE
Availability: Portions of paper copy and microfiche are illegible

Abstract: UNDER CENTRALLY FUNDED TECHNICAL SERVICES CONTRACT (INITIATED FY 68), INTERNATIONAL CENTER FOR AQUACULTURE ESTABLISHED AT AUBURN UNIVERSITY, AND PERMANENT STAFF OF AQUACULTURE SPECIALISTS MADE AVAILABLE TO CONDUCT IN-COUNTRY SURVEYS ON NEED AND POTENTIAL FOR FISH PRODUCTION IN LDC'S. CONTRACT ALSO SUPPORTS SHORT-TERM TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE IN SPECIALIZED AREAS, INCLUDING FISH TAXONOMY, FEEDS, FISH PROCESSING, LIMNOLOGY, FISH PARASITES AND DISEASES, RESERVOIR MANAGEMENT, WATER CHEMISTRY, AND FISHERIES BIOLOGY. TO EASE ACQUISITION OF LONG-TERM SERVICES, A BASIC ORDERING AGREEMENT WAS EXECUTED 6/69, WHEREBY MISSIONS MAY WRITE TASK ORDERS WITH AUBURN. IN JUNE 70, AID EXTENDED 5 YEAR INSTITUTIONAL GRANT (211D) TO IMPROVE AUBURN'S COMPETENCE IN AQUACULTURE. THIS PROGRAM, WHICH IS RELATED TO, BUT NOT A SPECIFIC PART OF THE PROJECT, WILL EMPHASIZE 1)IMPROVEMENT OF ON-CAMPUS RESEARCH; 2)DEVELOPMENT OF INFORMATION MATERIALS CENTER; 3)SPECIAL TRAINING FOR FOREIGN NATIONALS; 4)DEVELOPMENT OF AQUACULTURE PROJECT DESIGN AND METHODOLOGIES. SPECIFICALLY, AUBURN WILL PROVIDE 1)SHORT-TERM (1 MONTH) SURVEYS TO DETERMINE AQUACULTURE POTENTIAL OF LDC'S; 2)ON-CAMPUS TECHNICAL CONSULTATION FOR PROGRAMS ABROAD; 3)ON-CAMPUS ANALYSIS OF DATA; 4)DEVELOPMENT AND DISSEMINATION OF TECHNICAL INFORMATION AND TRAINING MATERIALS; 5)ORGANIZATION OF SHORT COURSES, SEMINARS, AND WORKSHOPS AT REQUEST OF AID/W; AND 6)SHORT-TERM CONSULTATION ON AQUACULTURAL PROBLEMS. AQUACULTURAL SURVEYS AND RELATED ACTIVITIES CARRIED ON IN THE FOLLOWING COUNTRIES: BRAZIL, JAPAN, PHILIPPINES, TAIWAN, VIETNAM, THAILAND, MALAYSIA, NEPAL, EAST PAKISTAN, INDIA, HONG KONG, SENEGAL, CAMEROON, CENTRAL AFRICAN REPUBLIC, TOGO, NIGERIA, GHANA; KENYA, IVORY COAST, GUYANA, COLOMBIA, ECUADOR, PERU, PANAMA, PARAGUAY, ISRAEL, EL SALVADOR, COSTA RICA, NICARAGUA, HAITI, PUERTO RICO, AND TURKEY.

Abstract: GRANT TO THE ORGANIZATION OF CENTRAL AMERICAN STATES  (ODECA)  TO DEVELOP A LOOSE-LEAF SERVICE  (LLS)  WITHIN ITS LEGAL PUBLICATIONS SERVICE.THE LLS WILL DISTRIBUTE A LOOSE-LEAF PUBLICATION OF LEGAL INFORMATION PERTINENT TO THE CENTRAL AMERICAN COMMON MARKET  (CACM) PLUS PERIODIC UPDATES TO LAWYERS, BUSINESSMEN, AND GOVT OFFICIALS ON A SUBSCRIPTION BASIS. AID (ROCAP)FUNDING PROVIDES ADDITIONAL STAFF (DOCUMENTATION CLERK,LAWYER),US CONSULTANTS,AND CONTRACTS WITH PRIVATE CENTRAL AMERICAN LEGAL SPECIALISTS TO PREPARE THE INITIAL PUBLICATION AND MAINTAIN THE SERVICE. ODECA LEGAL PUBLICATIONS SERVICE STAFF WILL COMPILE CACM LEGAL INFORMATION (TEXTS OF TREATIES,COMMENTARIES,ANALYSES,OPINIONS,AND INTERPRETATIONS)AND THEN ISSUE A ROUGH DRAFT OF THESE MATERIALS TO A LIMITED NUMBER OF CENTRAL AMERICANS INCLUDING THE PROJECT-CONTRACTED SPECIALISTS. THESE SPECIALISTS WILL ADVISE ON THE ACCURACY OF THE MATERIALS AND PREPARE ADDITIONAL MATERIALS FOR INCLUSION IN THE INITIAL LOOSE-LEAF PUBLICATION. WITH US CONSULTANT ASSISTANCE,THE FINAL DRAFT WILL BE READIED FOR PUBLICATION. AID PROVIDES FUNDS TO COVER THE FIRST-YEAR PRINTING AND DISTRIBUTION OF THE PUBLICATION AND COMPLEMENTARY FUNDING FOR THESE ACTIVITIES DURING SUBSEQUENT YEARS. US CONSULTANTS WILL PROVIDE ON-THE-JOB TRAINING TO ODECA STAFF TO ASSURE THE CONTINUATION OF THE LLS.

Abstract: UNIV OF UTAH CONTRACTED TO PROVIDE TA TO HAILE SELASSIE I UNIVERSITY (HSIU), GOVT OF ETHIOPIA (GOE) TO ESTAB A COLL FOR TCHR EDUC DURING 1960-72. COLLEGE TRAINS SECONDARY SCHOOL TEACHERS & ELEM SCHL ADMIN. HSIU CONTRIB FACULTY, TRNG DIRECTOR, STAFF & INSTRUCT SPACE. GOE PROVIDES EDUC PERSONNEL TO PLAN CURRIC, RECRUIT CANDIDATES & EVALUATE PROGRAM YEARLY. GOE ALSO PROVIDES 1 IN-SERVICE OFFICER FROM EACH OF THE PROVINCES, 6 KEY STAFF MBRS FOR SUMMER PROG INSR STAFF & MATERIALS. BEGUN IN 1962, PROJ IN 1970-71 GRADUATED 70 SECONDARY TCHRSEACH YR; IN 71, 89 TECH TCHRS RECD DIPLOMAS. TECH EDUC BLDG CONSTR. TCHRS COLL HAD HIGHEST % ETHIOPIAN PERSONNEL TCHING WITHIN HSIU. PROJ TERMINATED 1971. OTHER DONORS: UN, BRITISH

Abstract: PROJECT IS PROGRESSING SATISFACTORILY AND SHOULD BE COMPLETED WITHIN THE SCHEDULED 12/31/69 TERMINATION DATE. SUBSEQUENT TO THE PREPARATION OF THE DEVELOPMENT LOAN PAPER, USAID/B AGREED TO FINANCE A LOAN FOR NCR $4 MILLION OF LOCAL COSTS TO PARTIALLY OFFSET A GOB CONTRIBUTION WHICH WAS ORIGINALLY PROGRAMED BUT LATER CANCELLED. CONSTRUCTION ON THE MAIN SYSTEM HAS BEEN PRACTICALLY COMPLETED EXCEPT FOR THE 185 KMS SOUTHERN TERMINUS WHICH CONNECTS THE CAPIVARI DAM, ANOTHER COPEL PROJECT. DAM CONSTRUCTION IS ABOUT 6 MONTHS BEHIND SCHEDULE; THEREFORE CONSTRUCTION ON THE SOUTHERN TERMINUS IS BEING DEFERRED UNTIL PROGRESS ON THE DAM ADVANCES. DESPITE THIS DELAY, THE MAIN SYSTEM WILL BE COMPLETED ON SCHEDULE. 4 OF THE 5 ISOLATED SYSTEMS HAVE BEEN COMPLETED AND ARE NOW IN OPERATION. THE FIFTH IS SCHEDULED FOR COMPLETION IN 3/68. FAVORABLE PROGRESS HAS LIKEWISE BEEN MADE UNDER THE ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANCE AND TRAINING ASPECT OF THIS PROJECT. HOWEVER, COPEL'S ACTUAL OPERATING REVENUES AND PROFIT ARE CONSIDERABLY BELOW THE PROJECTIONS IN THE DEVELOPMENT LOAN PAPER. COPEL MAY NOT BE GENERATING SUFFICIENT FUNDS TO REPAY THE LOAN. AUDITORS RECOMMEND A FINANCIAL REVIEW OF THE PROJECT.

Abstract: GRANT TO PROVIDE FINANCIAL SUPPORT AND TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE TO ESTABLISH OFFICE OF MANPOWER AND LABOR AFFAIRS (OMLA) IN ODECA. OMLA WORKS TO INTEGRATE, COORDINATE INDIVIDUAL NATIONAL MANPOWER PROGRAMS INTO ORGANIZED EFFORT FOR REGIONAL DEVELOPMENT, PROVIDING BASE FOR REGIONAL MANPOWER PLANNING AND PERMITTING FREE MOBILITY OF WORK FORCE. OMLA WORKS FOR REGIONAL MANPOWER SERVICES STRUCTURE, DEVELOPS SKILL TRAINING PROGRAMS, IMPROVES MANPOWER PLANNING, UPGRADES MINISTRY OF LABOR CAPABILITY TO SUPPORT NATIONAL PROGRAMS. OMLA IS SECRETARIAT TO COUNCIL OF LABOR AND SOCIAL WELFARE IN ODECA, PROVIDING STAFF SERVICES, RESEARCH AND ANALYSIS, SPECIAL SERVICES TO SECRETARY-GENERAL. NATIONAL HUMAN RESOURCES COUNCILS, WHICH MAINTAIN CLOSE LIAISON WITH OMLA, ARE FORMED TO INSURE NATIONAL MANPOWER PLANNING. ROCAP SUPPORTS 2 OPERATING POSITIONS IN OMLA, WITH ROCAP MANPOWER ADVISOR COORDINATING PROJECT. ASSISTANCE SHIFTS IN LAST YEAR OF PROJECT, HOWEVER, TO SPECIALIZED HELP IN EACH PROGRAM AREA AND GREATER REGIONAL RESPONSIBILITY FOR ODECA. ODECA ASSUMES FULL OPERATIONAL SUPPORT OF OMLA BY 1969, AND MINISTRIES OF LABOR SUPPORT, IMPLEMENT REGIONALLY STRUCTURED PROGRAMS ON NATIONAL BASIS. ILO/OAS CONTRIBUTE FUNDS. OMLA CONDUCTS REGIONAL SEMINARS IN HUMAN RESOURCE DEVELOPMENT, APPRENTICESHIP TRNG, MINIMUM WAGE STANDARDS, LABOR STATISTICS, LABOR LEADERSHIP PARTICIPATION IN DEVELOPMENT, COMPARATIVE ANALYSIS OF LABOR MINISTRY ADMINISTRARIVE STRUCTURES, REGIONAL TEXTBOOKS AND VOCATIONAL TEACHER TRAINING CENTERS, APPRENTICESHIP INSTITUTES. OMLA DEVELOPS UNIFORM REGIONAL LABOR STATISTICS, COORDINATES MANPOWER RESEARCH, ANALYSIS, PLANNING; DEVELOPS REGIONAL CONVENTIONS TO ENCOURAGE UNIFORMITY IN LABOR LEGISLATION, COORDINATED REGIONAL PLAN FOR SKILL TRNG, REGIONAL NETWORK OF EMPLOYMENT SERVICES AND RELATED ACTIVITIES. LABORERS BENEFIT FROM FREEK, LARGER MKT FOR SKILLS, NEW OPPORTUNITIES FOR TRNG. 11/24/70 PROP REVISION EXTENDED OMLA BUDGET SUPPORT UNTIL CY72 TO COMPLETE COMPARATIVE STUDY ON SOCIAL COSTS OF PRODUCTION AND TO PREPARE PLAN FOR DEVELOPMENT OF NATIONAL EMPLOYMENT SERVICES AND SKILL TRAINING POLICIES.

Abstract: FINANCL, TECHL, COMMOD ASSISTNC AND PARTIC TRNG TO CSUCA TO SUPPORT PART OF REGNL INTEGRATN PLAN FOR HGHR EDUC IN CNTRL AMER COUNTRIES OF COSTA RICA, EL SALVADOR, HONDURAS, NICARAGUA, GUATEMALA, PANAMA. SUBPRO J CONTINUES & EXPANDS EDUC PROGR OF THE REGNL SCHL OF SANITARY ENGRG & WTR RSORCS  (ERIS) ,SAN CARLOS UNIVERSITY  (SCU) ,GUATEMALA TO PROVIDE MANPOWER TRND IN ALL PHASES IMPLMNTATN SANITATN ENGRG PROJS. TO IMPROVE ERIS,7 EXISTING COURSES WILL BE REVISED,9 NEW COURSES ADDED,ALL GEARED TO SPECIFIC REGNL NEEDS.ERIS WILL AWARD MASTER'S DEGREE,PLAN FOR FUTURE PHD PROGR.2-3 SHORT,NON-FORMAL COURSES WILL TR AIN 60 AUXIL & SUPPORT PERSONNEL PER YEAR IN ENVIRNMTL & PUB HLTH ENGRG,RUR WTR SUPPLY,OP/MAINTNCE OF SANITATN WORKS.ERIS PLANS TO GRADUATE 20 STUDENTS PER YR;FACULTY WILL BE INCRSD TO 6 FULL-TIME,8 PART-TIME MBRS. TEACHING AIDS & TECHNIQUES,LABORATORIES,ERIS LIBRARY & APPLIED RESEARCH FACILS WILL BE UPGRADED. APPLIED RES WILL BE CONDUCTED ON WASTE TREATMENT,OXIDATION PONDS,ENVIRONMENTAL HLTH,WTR TREATMNT FACILS CNSTRCTN,WTR DEMAND. A DEPT OF WTR RSORCS WILL BE ESTAB WITHIN ERIS & A TECHNICAL INFO SRVC WILL BE DEVELOPED FOR DISSEMINATION OF INFO ON WTR SUPPLY,WTR RSORCS,WASTE DISPOSAL SYSTEMS,WTR AND AIR POLLUTION CNTRL METHODS. ANNUAL CONFERENCES WILL BE HELD ON SUBJS SUCH AS STREAM POLLUTN,WTR RSORCS DEVEL,RUR WTR SUPPLY,SEWER SYS FINANCE,WATERSHED DEVEL,WTR FLOURIDATN,WELL-DRILLING AS APPLIED TO REGNL PROBS.ALSO,AN EXCHANGE PROG FOR VSTNG PROFSSRS WILL BE INSTITUTED. ROCAP WILL FUND CSUCA WHICH WILL CONTRACT WITH UNIV OF NORTH CAROLINA FOR FIELD COORDINATH,PARTIC TRNG,TECH ASSIST TO SCU;SCU WILL CONDUCT REGNL PROGS WITH EACH OF THE NATL UNIVS & WTR SUPPLY AGENCIES IN THE CNTRL AMER REGN.AS ROCAP SUPPORT DECREASES,CSUCA WILL DEVEL ALTERNATV SELF-FINANC SCHEMES BASED ON MBR COUNTRY SUPPORT TO ASSURE CONTINUING ERIS DEVEL & FUNC. PROAG 3/11/70 EXTENDED UNIV OF NORTH CAROLINA FOR AN ADDITNL YR. PROP 12/24/70 SUMMARIZES OBJECTIVES AND ACCOMPLISHMENTS 1965-70. MOST OBJECTIVES BEING MET OR EXCEEDED; STRONG EMPHASIS PLACED ON DEVEL REGNL GOVTS,UNIVS,AGENCIES COOP. PRIMARY/SECNDRY BENEFICIARIES: STUDENTS/REGNL POPULTN RECEIVG POTABLE WTR.

Abstract: GRANT AND CONTRACT TECHNICAL ADVISORY ASSISTANCE IS PROVIDED TO THE GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (GOI) TO EXPAND INDIA'S EXPORTS, THEREBY INCREASING FOREIGN EXCHANGE EARNINGS, DECREASING DEBT, AND REDUCING DEPENDENCE ON FOREIGN AID. NINE ANALYSES AND 17 COMMODITY SURVEYS WILL BE PERFORMED TO DIAGNOSE IMPEDIMENTS TO EXPORT EXPANSION AND TO IDENTIFY SPECIFIC COMMODITIES WHERE GOI HAS PRODUCT-MARKETING ADVANTAGES. THE SURVEYS WILL DESCRIBE WORLDWIDE SUPPLY/DEMAND, INDIA'S POSITION THEREIN, AND MAKE SPECIFIC RECOMMENDATIONS FOR INVESTMENTS AND POLICIES TO EXPAND EXPORTS. SUBJECT MATTER OF THE SURVEYS WILL INCLUDE: SPICES, FRUITS, VEGETABLES, SEAFOOD, MACHINE TOOLS, MINERALS, LEATHERS, TEXTILES, JUTE, COTTON, TEA, NUTS, OILCAKES, EXPORT TRANSPORTATION SYSTEMS, CARGO PROCEDURES AND DOCUMENTATION SIMPLIFICATION, MARKETING, AND FINANCIAL INCENTIVES. A CROSS-SECTIONAL ANALYSIS OF THESE SURVEYS WILL BE DONE TO IDENTIFY COMMON OBSTACLES AFFECTING EXPORTS. IN ADDITION, A COMPREHENSIVE REVIEW OF INDIA'S TRADE PROSPECTS WITH 25 INDIAN OCEAN BASIN COUNTRIES WILL BE PERFORMED. AS OPPORTUNITIES ARE IDENTIFIED, INDIAN BUSINESSMEN WILL VISIT FOREIGN MARKETS TO ORIENT THEMSELVES TO PRACTICES AND POSSIBILITIES FOR EXPORT. THREE PASA TECHNICIANS WILL IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF EXPORT STATISTICS, MARKET INFORMATION, AND COMMERCIAL INTELLIGENCE. A LARGE-SCALE PARTICIPANT TRAINING PROGRAM WILL BE INSTITUTED FOR GOI OFFICIALS IN THE AREAS OF EXPORT TRANSPORTATION, BANKING, AND INTERNATIONAL MARKETING. TO ASSIST THE PRIVATE EXPORT SECTOR IN MAKING SOUND POLICY AND INVESTMENT DECISIONS, THE GOI WILL IMPROVE INFORMATION SERVICES AND REGULATORY PRACTICES. A CREDIT INSTITUTION WILL ALSO BE ESTABLISHED TO PROVIDE FINANCIAL SERVICES TO THE EXPORT COMMUNITY. PROAG 5/7/70 ESTABLISHES A GOI FOREIGN TRADE RESEARCH AND ANALYSIS UNIT AT THE INDIAN INSTITUTE OF FOREIGN TRADE, AND UPDATES UNIVERSITY COURSES IN INTERNATIONAL TRADE FINANCE AND COMMERCIAL POLICY. PROAG 5/24/71 ESTABISHES A TRADE INFORMATION CENTER, AND ADDS ADDITIONAL SURVEYS AND TOURS.

Abstract: GRANT PROVIDED TO GOVERNMENT OF PAKISTAN (GOP) TO IMPROVE THE MANAGERIAL CAPABILITIES OF KEY GOP OFFICIALS. PROJECT ACTIVITIES INCLUDE THE DEVELOPMENT OF CAREER PLANNING PROGRAMS, THE STRENGTHENING OF PAKISTANI INSTITUTIONS WHICH EDUCATE AND TRAIN GOP OFFICIALS, AND THE INTRODUCTION OF MORE PROGRESSIVE PERSONNEL MANAGEMENT PRACTICES. CAREER PLANNING PROGRAMS WILL BE DEVELOPED FOR THE GOP'S ESTABLISHMENT DIVISION IN THE AREAS OF RURAL ADMINISTRATION,URBAN ADMINISTRATION,MUNICIPAL (SMALLER COMMUNITIES) ADMINISTRATION,PLANNING & FINANCE,& PUBLIC ENTERPRISE. 20 PARTICIPANTS EACH YEAR WILL RECEIVE IN-COUNTRY,& FOREIGN TRAINING,& WILL BE PLACED IN KEY GOP POSITIONS UPON THEIR RETURN. PAKISTANI INSTITUTIONS WILL BE STRENGTHENED BY FIRMING UP THE ROLE OF THE NATIONAL TRAINING COUNCIL,HOLDING PERIODIC MEETINGS OF THE DIRECTORS OF PAKISTAN'S INSTITUTIONS,& DEVELOPING AN EXCHANGE PROGRAM FOR FACULTY. ALSO,A SYSTEM OF EXCHANGE OF RESEARCH WILL BE ESTABLISHED,SPECIALIZATIONS WILL BE DEVELOPED WITHIN THE INSTITUTES,& ORGANIZATION & MANAGEMENT TRAINING UNITS WILL BE ESTABLISHED IN MAJOR GOP AGENCIES & PUBLIC CORPORATIONS. INSTITUTIONS SUCH AS THE BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION INSTITUTE OF THE UNIVERSITY OF PANJAB,THE CIVIL SERVICE ACADEMY,& THE NATIONAL INSTITUTES OF PUBLIC ADMINISTRATION WILL BE STRENGTHENED IN THE AREAS OF PRE-SERVICE EDUCATION,PRE-SERVICE TRAINING,IN-HOUSE TRAINING,& MID-CAREER DEVELOPMENT. PROGRESSIVE PERSONNEL MANAGEMENT PRACTICES SUCH AS MANPOWER PLANNING & EVALUATION,POSITION CLASSIFICATION,TRAINING NEEDS,SURVEY TECHNIQUES,&EVALUATION OF TRAINING PROGRAMS,WILL BE INTRODUCED INTO THE GOP'S ESTABLISHMENT DIVISION. CONTRACTOR PROVIDES SHORT-TERM CONSULTANTS,& AID PROVIDES PARTICIPANT TRNG IN US & ABROAD,IN-COUNTRY TRNG,& VEHICLES. HOST COUNTRY PROVIDES TRNG FACILITIES,PERSONNEL FOR TRNG,OFFICE SPACE & EQUIPMENT,& A CO-DIRECTOR FOR PROJECT. PRIMARY BENEFICIARIES WILL BE TRAINED GOP OFFICIALS,& PAKISTANI CIVIL SERVICE ALSO BENEFITS. IN SUBSEQUENT PROPS OF 10/1/69,5/25/70,&1/26/71,PROJECT WAS EXTENDED 1 YEAR &GOAL WAS EXPANDED TO INCLUDE IMPROVEMENT OF TECHNICAL SKILLS,CAREER PLANNING PROGRAMS WERE EXPANDED,PARTIC'S INCREASED.

Abstract: TECHNICAL ADVISORY ASSISTANCE IS PROVIDED TO THE EAST AFRICAN RAILWAYS & HARBORS (EAR&H) TO ESTABLISH SEPARATE SUPPLY DEPARTMENTS FOR ITS RAILWAYS AND HARBORS SERVICES. EAR&H IS A NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATION (PART OF THE EAST AFRICAN COMMUNITY) RESPONSIBLE FOR RAILWAYS,PORTS AND MOTOR TRANSPORT SERVICES IN KENYA, UGANDA AND TANZANIA AS WELL AS MARINE SERVICES ON LAKES TANGANYILA AND VICTORIA. THE SEPARATION OF EAR&H'S SUPPLY DEPARTMENT IS PART OF THE LARGER UP-COMING REORGANIZATION OF EAR&H INTO SEPARATE CORPORATIONS -- THE EAST AFRICAN RAILWAYS CORP WITH HEADQUARTERS IN NAIROBI AND THE EAST AFRICAN HARBORS CORP WITH HEADQUARTERS IN DAR ES SALAAM. TWO US SUPPLY MANAGEMENT CONSULTANTS WILL BE ASSIGNED TO EACH NEW CORPORATION ASSISTING IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF EFFECTIVE SUPPLY ORGANIZATION,OPERATING AND ADMINISTRATIVE SYSTEMS. RELATED PROCEDURES AND FORMS WILL BE DEVELOPED FOR EACH DEPARTMENT. THE RAILWAY CORP'S DATA PROCESSING CENTER WILL BE UTILIZED FOR RAILWAY SUPPLY PROCEDURES IN THOSE INSTANCES IN WHICH COMPUTERIZATION WOULD BE EFFECTIVE AND ECONOMICAL. A REGIONAL SUPLY ORGANIZATION IS ALSO PLANNED FOR THE RAILWAY CORP. TWO COUNTERPARTS WILL WORK ON A FULL-TIME BASIS AS UNDERSTUDIES TO THE SUPPLY CONSULTANTS. THE CONSULTANTS WILL ALSO ASSIST IN DEVELOPING STAFF RE-TRAINING PROGRAMS FOR BOTH MANAGEMENT AND LOCAL SUPPLY LEVELS. ACTIVITIES UNDERTAKEN BY THE US CONSULTANTS WILL BE COORDINATED WITH THE UNITED NATIONS DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM'S (UNDP) EAR&H TRAINING AND DEVELOPMENT PROJECT WHICH ENCOMPASSES MANAGEMENT ANALYSIS SERVICES, A CENTRAL ELECTRONIC COMPUTER AND DATA PROCESSING SERVICE,RESEARCH PLANNING AND DEVELOPMENT,CENTRAL STATISTICAL SERVICES AND PUBLIC RELATIONS. UNDP-PROVIDED EXPERTISE, TRAINING FACILITIES & EQUIPMENT WILL BE AVAILABLE TO THE AID CONSULTANTS. EAR&H WILL PROVIDE PERSONNEL, INSTITUTIONAL SUPPORT AND LIMITED FINANCIAL SUPPORT. PRIMARY BENEFICIARIES ARE EAR&H OFFICIALS FOR WHOM IMPROVED SUPPLY MANAGEMENT SKILLS AND PROCEDURES ARE PROVIDED.

Abstract: BEGUN IN 1958, PROJECT EMPHASIS SHIFTED EARLY 1970S FROM ERADICATION TO CONTROL OF MALARIA AND OTHER COMMUNICABLE DISEASES. PROGRAM CONDUCT CONFORMS TO 4 PHASES WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION'S METHODS FOR MALARIA ERADICATION: PREPARATORY PHASE-MALARIA SURVEY, GEOGRAPH RECON, NATIONAL STAFF TRAINING, LOGISTICS; ATTACK PHASE-REDUCE DISEASE TRANSMISSION THRU INSECTICIDE HOUSE SPRAYING, FOLLOW-UP DETECTION/TREATMENT; CONSOLIDATION PHASE-WITHDRAW SPRAYING, INTENSIFY SURVEILLANCE WORK THRU HOUSE VISITATION ELIMINATING RESIDUAL CASES IN POPULATION WITH RADICAL DRUG TREATMENT; MAINTENANCE PHASE-GON'S GENERAL HEALTH SERVICE PREVENTS MALARIA REINTRODUCTION. ESTIMATES PLACE 80% OF POPULATION WITHIN CONSOLIDATION PHASE BY 1972

Abstract: GRANT PROVIDED TO THE GOVERNMENT OF LIBERIA TO CONDUCT A DEMOGRAPHIC SURVEY. THE HOUSEHOLD SURVEY WILL CANVASS A 5% SAMPLE OF THE POPULATION AND WILL BE CONDUCTED 4 TIMES PER YEAR DURING EACH OF THE 5 YEARS OF THE PROJECT. SURVEY WILL COLLECT INFORMATION RELATING TO INFANT MORTALITY RATES, FERTILITY RATES, MIGRATION RATES, HOUSEHOLD COMPOSITION, AND GENERAL POPULATION TRENDS. USAID WILL PROVIDE THE BULK OF THE FINANCING. A US BUREAU OF CENSUS PASA EXPERT WILL DEVELOP SAMPLING PROCEDURES AND SURVEY QUESTIONNAIRES. IN ADDITION, HE WILL ASSIST THE LIBERIAN BUREAU OF STATISTICS IN SELECTING AND TRAINING PERSONNEL TO CARRY OUT SURVEY INCLUDING 9 REGIONAL INSPECTORS, 27 CREW LEADERS AND 110 ENUMERATORS. 6 PARTICIPANTS WILL RECEIVE 2-9 MONTH US TRAINING. BY END OF PROJECT, LIBERIA BUREAU OF STATISTICS SHOULD BE ABLE TO CONTINUE SURVEY ACTIVITIES. PRO AG 1/21/72 PROVIDES FOR AN ADDITIONAL SOCIO-ECONOMIC STUDY OF THE UPPER LOFA REGION. THE COMPREHENSIVE, INTERDISCIPLINARY STUDY WILL ASSESS THE REGION'S AGRICULTURAL, NATURAL, AND HUMAN RESOURCES AND RECOMMEND AN INTEGRATED DEVELOPMENT PLAN. STUDY WILL BE FINANCED BY THE LIBERIAN IRON AND STEEL CORP., THE LIBERIAN PRODUCE AND MARKETING CORP., THE UNITED NATIONS DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM, AND USAID.
